                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and here we're going to delete the episode view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the right-hand panel of our split container."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Instead, what we're going to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is create the episode view and the podcast view in code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're not going to use the designer for these"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because we want to actually switch a different view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in and out of the right-hand panel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""When we create these two controls though,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we will need to remember to set that dock style to fill,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so that they fill the entire right-hand panel"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the split container."",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we need to go and look at what happens"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when this selected tree node changes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If it's an episode that's been selected,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we'll clear whatever control is in the right-hand panel"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our split container,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll add in the episode for your user control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we need to do a similar thing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if a podcast tree node is selected"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if the selected node was for a podcast"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""again, we'll clear the right hand panel,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll add the podcast view in."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we do need to remember at this point"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to update the podcast view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to show the podcast that's been selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this time we're not going to use that hacky method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of making all of it's private controls public."",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll put a method on the podcast view called set podcast,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll pass in the podcast that's been selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Inside that view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can just then go to the two labels,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and set up their properties."",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The podcast title,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the number of episodes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the podcast that's been selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we're ready to run our application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as you can see, when we select a podcast node"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we see our new podcast view in the right-hand panel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if we select an episode node,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.4818671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""episode view appears on the right."",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.4818671
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Summary"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m2&clip=11&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's just review what we've learned in this module."",
                          ""displayTime"": 0.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We looked first at the topic of resizing."",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""How you can make sure that your application still looks good"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whether it's sized very small or really large."",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also discussed layouts."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""How you can make the best use of the available space"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that your application has."",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we discussed a few different options"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you have for layout."",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so the two best practices"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that I've been wanting to demonstrate in this module"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as we've updated our my podcasts demo application, is first,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""make sure your application resizes really well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""That involves making use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the anchor and dock properties on controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to keep them the right distance"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the edge of their containers."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It also involves using appropriate minimum and maximum sizes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on controls, containers, and forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we also saw in action some of the layout panels"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can make use of to help you with resizing,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as the TableLayoutPanel,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the FlowLayoutPanel,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the SplitContainer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And second, make good use of space"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with an appropriate layout."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if your application is quite complicated,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and has lots of different data views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then you may need to use dockable windows,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like Visual Studio, to allow users to have many views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""accessible all at the same time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or if your application has got"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a very large number of commands for manipulating data,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then you may find that the Windows ribbon control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is what you need."",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But probably for the majority of applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the simple TabControl for switching between open documents,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or a small number of different views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will be more than sufficient."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally we looked at the most popular of layouts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for Windows Forms applications,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's an explorer style layout."",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Which allows you to navigate between different data views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for many different items in your tree control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In the next module, we're going to be looking at more ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in which we can make our application more usable,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.3259894
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and accessible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.3259894
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  ""title"": ""Usability, Accessibility, and Localization"",
                  ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=0&mode=live"",
                  ""clips"": [
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Introduction"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=0&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Hi, my name's Mark Heath,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and in this module of our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms Best Practices course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to be looking at the topics of usability,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""accessibility, and localization."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let me just give you a quick overview"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the things we'll be covering in this module."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're going to look at the topic of usability,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is really about how easy is it for users to accomplish"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what they're trying to do with our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Can we help them to fall into the pit of success,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where it's easy for them to do the right thing,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and hard for them to do the wrong thing."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""How discoverable is our application?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And by that I mean, do they need to get training"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or read a manual before they can do anything,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or is it simply obvious how to make use of the features"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the application offers."",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll also talk about accessibility,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and here we're going to look at how we can make it possible"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for users to navigate our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""without having to make use of the mouse."",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll also look at how we can help users who want to make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""use of large font sizes and high contrast color schemes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and make sure that our application works well for them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll also discuss how users"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""who are blind or visually impaired,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""only making use of screen reading software,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can also be helped by the way we write our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, we'll look at localization."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""How can we support users who speak other languages,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or maybe who speak the same language,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but are in a different culture?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we'll be looking at different ways that we can make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""translations of the resource files in our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I will be demonstrating all the principles we look at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by updating our demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to put some of them into practice."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.0
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Accessibility"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=1&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, we're going to start off by looking at accessibility,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and in particular, how we can update our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to work with well with large font sizes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and high contrast color schemes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, it's possible that you may not be aware"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that in Windows you can set up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what's called a high contrast color scheme."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It doesn't look particularly pretty, but for some users"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this is gonna make it much more easy"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for them to read what's on the screen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, if we want to be able to detect in code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whether a high contrast color scheme is being used,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we can make use of SystemInformation.HighContrast,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll see that in action in a demo shortly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also, Windows gives you the ability to adjust the font sizes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you used in your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, to a certain extent, this should just work."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If the user sets these font sizes larger,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the text in your application should just get bigger"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""without you having to do anything,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's in part due to the auto scale mode property"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of container controls in Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You may notice in the designer when you create a new form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that it sets the auto scale mode to font for you."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If however, for some reason, you need to discover"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your application whether large fonts are being used,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then one of the ways you can do that is to examine"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the DPI setting of a graphics subject"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you create on your form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And what about ScreenReader support?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, ScreenReader applications will actually be able to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""infer some information from your Windows Forms application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""without you having to do anything,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because it can use reflection to look at the contents"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of your form and see where there are labels and text boxes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and see what their names are."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But each control in Windows Forms has some properties"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are particularly intended"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for ScreenReader's to make use of."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""These are the AccessibleName,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which tells you what the control is."",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The AccessibleDescription,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is often the same really as the AccessibleName,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but allows you to say what it looks like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the AccessibleRole,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which you select from a list and tells the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ScreenReader software what sort of control it is,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so if you're willing to take the time to fill in"",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""these properties, users of ScreenReader software"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will have a much better experience."",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's have a look at our demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and see how well it does when we use large fonts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.0163223
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and a high contrast color theme."",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.0163223
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Accessibility"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=2&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, here I have our demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's running in a virtual machine,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is a great way to do testing if you want to set"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your Windows settings to something"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a bit out of the ordinary."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, let's go to the Windows Control Panel now,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we will switch to a high contrast color theme."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's go back to our demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and see what it looks like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as you can see, we've got a few problems."",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Our tree view control is working just fine,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the text inside our text box is,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but all labels are invisible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the trouble is, is because we've explicitly set"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the background color of this form to white,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it means we we can't see the white text"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on a white background."",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, let's fix that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so here we can see in the designer of the main form,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we've set the background color to be white."",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And although we didn't set the background color"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on any of the panels that are within it,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because the back color is what's called an ambient property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the panels and user controls that we've added"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the form have picked up that back color from the form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now there's two ways that we can fix this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we could go in and choose a system color"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""instead of explicitly setting a color."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we could choose something from here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""maybe this one, Window, which also happens to be white."",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But instead, let's set this back to the default property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll detect a high contrast color theme"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our code behind."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here, we'll only set the back color if we're not"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in a high contrast color theme."",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, let's see if that fixes the problem."",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now we can see, our labels and the button text"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are visible again."",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We probably also should've done the same thing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for this podcast title label,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which in the designer we'd explicitly set to be grey text."",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's switch back to a regular color theme,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll change the font size."",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll have to log off and log back on again."",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So hopefully you should notice already"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the Windows font sizes are a bit larger."",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's launch our application, and it should just work."",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Okay, so you can see here this application is taking up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a bit more space, and all the fonts are a bit bigger."",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you'll also notice that our resizing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we went through all that trouble in the last module"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to get just right, isn't working properly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Our tree view and the buttons underneath it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are still anchored to the edges"",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that they were anchored to before,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but Windows Forms has somehow got confused"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""about how far away from the edge of their container"",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they should be."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Another issue that we've now got,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that some of those minimum sizes that we set up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""now aren't quite right."",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, we set the minimum size of the left-hand panel"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the splitter control so that it wouldn't obscure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the add and remove buttons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But now the add and remove buttons are a bit wider,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that size isn't quite right anymore."",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, that's an example of where we might want to use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the DPI setting to calculate a value there."",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's just fix this resizing problem."",
                          ""displayTime"": 211.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now I must confess, I'm not entirely sure why"",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the split container has this problem with large font sizes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but there's a fairly easy fix."",
                          ""displayTime"": 222.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll just remove the designer from the equation,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just as we did with the right-hand panel,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 226.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we won't actually use the designer"",
                          ""displayTime"": 228.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to set the left-hand panel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Instead, we'll set it in the code behind."",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll create an instance of the subscription view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 238.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""dock it to fill,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then we'll add it to the left-hand side"",
                          ""displayTime"": 245.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the split container."",
                          ""displayTime"": 248.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's see if that fixes it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 252.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And here we have our application properly resizing now"",
                          ""displayTime"": 255.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with large fonts."",
                          ""displayTime"": 258.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as you can see from this brief demo, it was worth us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 263.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""taking the time to test our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 266.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with large font sizes and a high contrast color scheme,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 269.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as it revealed a couple of problems"",
                          ""displayTime"": 272.3017668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we could fix fairly easily."",
                          ""displayTime"": 274.3017668
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Keyboard Navigation"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=3&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, let's look at keyboard navigation now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Some users may want to be able to use our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just from the keyboard."",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now that might be for accessibility reasons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""They aren't able to, or don't want to use the mouse,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or it may simply be for productivity reasons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If your users are using your application everyday to perform"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""repetitive tasks, then they'll be very grateful"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if there are some keyboard shortcuts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that speed up their job for them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's have a look at a few ways in which we can make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our application accessible from the keyboard."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, you're probably aware that you can navigate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""between the controls in your application using the tab key."",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""As you press tab, you'll jump from one control to the next,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the focus will be set to those controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""allowing you to enter data, and to trigger buttons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this is something that WinForms provides for you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""automatically, but one thing you do need to check"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that you've got your tab order set up correctly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Usually, you'd set your tab order so that you'd go"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from left to right, and top to bottom."",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so you need to make sure that you've set"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the tab index property on all your controls appropriately."",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If there are controls on your form that you don't want"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be part of the tabbing experience,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""maybe to stop the user having to press tab"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""multiple times just to get through the controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then you can set the tab stop property to false"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for those controls that you don't need to be able to tab to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But what about the buttons on your application?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""How can you trigger them from the keyboard?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now there's a few ways that you do this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The first is to make use of what's called pneumonics."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we set the text on our play button to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""&Play,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then on the GUI, that ampersand won't actually be visible,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but when you press the ALT Key,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the letter p will be underlined."",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that indicates that if you now press p,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the play button will be triggered."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so you can quite easily make a shortcut key"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for all of your buttons just by choosing a unique letter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to use as its mnemonic."",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's another way as well that we can get shortcuts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""assigned to buttons that we saw in our first module,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's by making use of the accept button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and cancel button properties of a form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The button that we specify as the accept button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will be trigger by the enter key,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the button that we specify as the cancel button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will be triggered by the escape key."",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But what if you want to use a completely different key"",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as the shortcut key?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Maybe you wanted control, spacebar, to trigger playback."",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well what you need to be able to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to intercept key presses and examine them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to see if the shortcut key has been pressed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And there's a variety of ways you can do this in WinForms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but the way we're going to look at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is by overriding the forms process command key method."",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This will allow you to detect"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that your shortcut key combination"",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""has been pressed, and to trigger the action."",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if you want to trigger the action that's associated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with a button that's already on your form,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then one of the best ways of doing that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is by calling the perform click method on that button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The advantage of doing this, as opposed to just calling"",
                          ""displayTime"": 194.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that button's click event handler directly,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 197.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that if the button's disable at the time,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then nothing's going to happen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so this can prevent subtle bugs"",
                          ""displayTime"": 205.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where the user can launch an action associated with a button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""even though it's disabled by using it's shortcut key."",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, although our demo application doesn't have a menu,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you've got a menu in your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then Windows Forms has a really easy way"",
                          ""displayTime"": 221.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of associating shortcuts with menu options."",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Each menu item has a shortcut key's property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the Windows Forms designer has a nice view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 231.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that allows you to specify what the shortcut key"",
                          ""displayTime"": 234.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for any menu item is."",
                          ""displayTime"": 237.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Here we're accessing the shortcut key"",
                          ""displayTime"": 239.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to control q."",
                          ""displayTime"": 241.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the effects of doing this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 243.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that when you run the application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 245.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you bring down that shortcut menu,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it actually shows you as a hint what the shortcut key"",
                          ""displayTime"": 249.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for that menu option is."",
                          ""displayTime"": 253.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Which is really nice for users because they can easily learn"",
                          ""displayTime"": 254.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the shortcuts for your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 258.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And when you do this with menu items,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 260.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you don't have to do any work to wire up that shortcut key"",
                          ""displayTime"": 262.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the menu options."",
                          ""displayTime"": 265.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms will just do it for you automatically."",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a look at our demo application now,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 271.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and put into practice a few of these techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 273.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to make our application more easily usable"",
                          ""displayTime"": 277.8480668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just from the keyboard."",
                          ""displayTime"": 280.8480668
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Keyboard Navigation"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=4&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's have a look at tab order first."",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Here, I've loaded up the application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on our virtual machine again,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you maybe able to see that the control that's currently"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""got the focus is actually the remove button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if I were to press the spacebar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or enter key at the moment, it would actually trigger"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the remove feature and unsubscribe us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the podcast we've currently got selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I press the tab key, you'll see now"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the focus is moved to the add button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you may be able to see a small dotted rectangle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's showing us that that's the control with the focus."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's press tab again,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and now focus has gone to the tree view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I can use the arrow keys to navigate up and down"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the tree nodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I press tab again, now the tab focus is actually"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on this splitter bar of our split container."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So I can use the left and right arrows to resize"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the left and right views."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I press tab again, we'll get into the right-hand panel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The first control that's got the focus is the play button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the my tags text box."",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the my notes text box."",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the my rating control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now the favorite checkbox."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we've gone through all the controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if I press tab again,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're back to the remove button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now I don't think this is a particularly logical order,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so let's go and sort out the tab order."",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So in Visual Studio, it's quite straightforward"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to set the tab index property."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Here, the tab index of the tree view is seven,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""let me set that to one."",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'll set the add button to two"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the remove button to three."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""They don't actually have to be consecutive numbers,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it will just move from the lowest number"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the highest number."",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's do the same thing for the episode view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we can in fact, instead of going to each control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and typing in the number, use a feature in Visual Studio"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to make this a bit easier."",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We go view, tab order, and then we'll click the controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in order."",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Notice that I'm also clicking on the labels,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's going to be useful if we set mnemonics"",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the labels, because when we activate those mnemonics,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll automatically jump to the next control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, let's do that now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For my tags,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we use the shortcut key of t."",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The rating, r."",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For favorite, f."",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For notes, n."",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And for play, p."",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in the subscription view, add button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we use a."",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But for the remove button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""now we've got a little bit of a problem,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because we already used r for rating,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so we'd have to choose a different letter, like v."",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's run the application and see what effect those changes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""have made."",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So now when we launch our application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's the tree view that's go focus immediately."",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So I can just start pressing the up and down arrows"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to move around."",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now I tab to add, remove, the splitter bar,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 191.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and actually the splitter bar might be a good choice"",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to put tab stop to false on, because it's not really that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""important for keyboard navigation."",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then to tags, rating, favorite, and notes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I hold down the alt key, you'll see all the mnemonics"",
                          ""displayTime"": 209.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""have been underlined, showing me what I can press next."",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if I press t,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we jump straight to the my tags text box."",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I press alt p, it's going to trigger the play button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 222.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which launches the podcast in media player."",
                          ""displayTime"": 225.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So those changes are working well for us,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but let's just do one final thing."",
                          ""displayTime"": 231.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll add a custom shortcut to the play button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 233.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so you can press control and space to trigger playback."",
                          ""displayTime"": 236.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's override the process command key method."",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And while examining key data, and look for control space."",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we see that key combination, we'll simulate a click"",
                          ""displayTime"": 257.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the playback button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 260.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll return true to say that we've handled"",
                          ""displayTime"": 263.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this key combination."",
                          ""displayTime"": 265.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's run it and check it works."",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So I'm going to press control and space,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 271.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we can see it's triggered our playback action."",
                          ""displayTime"": 274.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We have however introduced a subtle bug,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 278.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""even despite using the perform click method."",
                          ""displayTime"": 281.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's if I navigate on to a podcast node in our tree,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 284.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this right-hand view hasn't got the play button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 288.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But if I press control space again,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 292.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's performed the click action on a button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 298.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's not even visible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 300.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So you do need to be careful with shortcut keys"",
                          ""displayTime"": 302.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you don't trigger actions that the user isn't suppose"",
                          ""displayTime"": 304.8680224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be able to access."",
                          ""displayTime"": 307.8680224
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Usability"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=5&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's turn our attention to the topic of usability."",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now to be honest, this is a huge subject,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and worthy of its own course."",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, Pluralsight have got several courses"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on user interface and user experience design,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's well worth your time watching those"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're designing user interfaces."",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But let's just spend a few minutes considering some"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the ways that we as Windows Forms developers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can help our users to be able to easily use our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now often as developers, we just assume that it's obvious"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how to use our applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We design the user interface that made sense to us,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we assume it will sense to our users."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But there's actually quite an easy way that we can test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that theory, and it's to do what's called a usability test."",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Find someone who's never used your application before,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""get them to sit down and try to use it,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you may be surprised at how difficult they find it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's consider a few principles and techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for how we can make our applications just a bit more usable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The first principle I'll mention is that of familiarity."",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Make use of things that your users already know."",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So use standard controls and dialogues,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if it's all possible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Don't make the users have to learn lots of new things."",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you need buttons, then use buttons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that look like buttons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Don't decide that you're just going to put labels"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the form that the user can click,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because it won't be obvious to them that they can do so."",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now this doesn't mean that your buttons have to look"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""dull and boring, you could style them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to look a bit more appealing than these basic ones."",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But if they look like buttons, the user will know"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that they can click them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the same applies for other controls as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you make use of controls that your users have seen before"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like combo boxes and tree views,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then it's going to be much easier"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for them to get started with your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The next principle I want to talk about is discoverability."",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's be honest, it's actually quite unlikely"",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that our users are going to read the documentation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""before they begin to use our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Instead, they're just gonna launch it up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and see if they can work out how to use it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now in the my podcasts demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we've been looking at as we've gone"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""through this course, probably the first thing the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is going to want to do, is to subscribe to a new podcast,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and maybe they'll want to unsubscribe"",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the default podcasts that we set up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when it runs for the first time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'm currently in our user interface,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you do that by clicking add and remove buttons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's not brilliant, these buttons don't actually"",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""use the words subscribe and unsubscribe,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but hopefully most users will be able to work out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that that's what these buttons are for."",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we were to decide that we want to start using"",
                          ""displayTime"": 179.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""icon buttons on a toolbar,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 182.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then although that might look a bit nicer,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it begins to introduce a problem."",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""How does the user determine what these are for?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In this case, probably the best solution would be"",
                          ""displayTime"": 192.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to put tooltips on the buttons to tell the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what will happen when they click them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But what if we decided we wanted to go even further,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""maybe instead of even having add and remove buttons,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we just got rid of them and decided that to subscribe"",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to a new podcast you could drag and drop a URL"",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from your browser into the tree view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Like you can see here in this screenshot."",
                          ""displayTime"": 217.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And maybe we decide that to unsuscribe,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 221.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you right-click the tree node of a podcast"",
                          ""displayTime"": 224.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and select it from a context menu."",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now drag and drop and context menus"",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are probably quite good additions to this application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But they do have a problem, they're not easily discoverable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 236.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's not obvious to the user that this is how you subscribe"",
                          ""displayTime"": 239.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this is how you unsubscribe."",
                          ""displayTime"": 243.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So be careful about making operations like these,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 245.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the only way that you expose certain key functions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 248.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of your application, or you're going to find"",
                          ""displayTime"": 251.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you've got some frustrated users who can't work out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 254.0921447
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what to do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 256.0921447
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Helping the User to Get it Right"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=6&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as we've said, usability is all about helping the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to get it right, helping them to use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our application successfully."",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'm going to list very quickly several ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in Windows Forms that we can achieve that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then we're going to go back to our demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and put a number of these into practice."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So there are lots of ways that you can explain to the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what's going on and how to use your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And tooltips are one way that we've already mentioned,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you can add these very easily with the tooltip component"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that comes with Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also, Windows Forms allows you to plum in"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the help system."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If the user presses F1, an events going to be raised"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we can handle, and you can also add a help button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to your form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Another useful technique is to have"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""first run tutorials or hints."",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So the first time the user runs your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""text appears or message boxes pop up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that give them some hints as to how to use your"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""application successfully, and what they need to do next."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Some operations in your application may have enough"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""complexity to require wizards that guide the users"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""through entering information step by step."",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if the user does enter something wrong,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""maybe on a form of data entry with lots of inputs,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's useful to indicate which field that got wrong,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and what the problem was."",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the Windows Forms error provider control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""allows you to do that, associating an error"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with a particular control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, in many line of business applications,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there'll be views or forms where the user has to enter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a large amount of data, maybe information about"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a customer or an order."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so again, it's gonna be very useful"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we can help them in those controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where they enter the data, not to enter the wrong thing."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if you've got a text box for text input,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then make use of properties like max length,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so that they can't enter more data"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""than the underlying database field will allow."",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or make use of the auto complete feature of text box,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with which you can prompt the user to reuse things"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that they entered before."",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you need to take numeric input,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you could use a text box for that,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but then you have to deal with what happens"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the user enters something that's not a number."",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms does actually come with a number of controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like the NumericUpDown, which you can see in our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""demo application for the rating."",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or even the track bar, which is a slider."",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The advantage of using these is, it's not possible"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to enter something that's out of range,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or that isn't a number."",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, this principle's even more important"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you need to take date input."",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Don't just give the user a text box,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because there is so many different ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""people can format dates, and there's a good chance"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you won't be able to interpret what the user's written."",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Instead, again Windows Forms comes with a couple of choices"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for entering dates, such as the DateTimePicker,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or the MonthCalendar."",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in fact, many third party control libraries for"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms provides you with some"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""really nice alternatives if you don't like the ones"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that come out of the box."",
                          ""displayTime"": 192.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But that's enough talking now,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we could go on giving many examples of ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in which you can help the user to enter the right data,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and to understand what they're suppose to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But let's take a few of these suggestions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that I've just given, and apply them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.1199892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.1199892
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Tooltips"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=7&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And yes, this is a very simple application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and most users would probably be able to guess"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how to use it, but it does still have"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a few usability issues."",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, have a look here in my tags."",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What are we suppose to enter in here?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I want to tag this podcast as being about DNSimple"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and Erlang, am I suppose to put a space between those,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or a comma?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's actually a comma in this application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but we haven't told the user that anywhere."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So how are they suppose to know?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""At the very least, we ought to offer them a tooltip"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on this text box to tell them that that's what"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they're suppose to do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's do that now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So the component we need to use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is the tooltip component, and we can drag one"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the toolbox on to any container control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like this user control here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we can easily add a tooltip to any of our controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""either from the designer, or from the code behind."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's add a tooltip for the tags text box."",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll add one for the play button as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll just do two for now, and let's check that works."",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when I select the tags text box,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I get some help as to what I should be entering,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and when I hover over the play button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.4731892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it tells me what's going to happen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.4731892
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - First Run and ErrorProvider"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=8&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also mentioned that you might want to help the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by showing them a brief tutorial"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on their first run of the application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a quick look at how we could do that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""One simple way to detect the first run of the application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to make use of the application settings"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that our Windows Forms project provides you with by default."",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we look up here in the properties folder,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can open this settings file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll create new settings called first run,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's a Boolean property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's default value is true."",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's go to the load event of our main form,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll see if we're running for the first time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we are, we'll show our welcome message in tutorial."",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll set the first run property to false,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we need to make sure we remember to save"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""those settings as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's use our virtual machine to run this application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and check that this first run setting works."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's launch our application for the first time,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we see our welcome message,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and now let's launch our same application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the second time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this time the welcome message doesn't appear."",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the final thing I want to demonstrate here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is the use of the error provider."",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now our demo application in one sense"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""isn't particularly well suited for using the error provider,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because there isn't a large amount of data entry in it,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and there aren't a lot of things you can get wrong."",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But just to show you the error provider in action,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll use it on this add new podcast form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""even though it's probably overkill."",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Like the tooltip, the error provider is a component"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can drag on to a form,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so let's do that now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll go into the okay button click handler,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and if the user hasn't entered a valid URL"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll use the error provider to tell them that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they've done something wrong."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so here we're using Uri.TryCreate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to see if the text that users entered can be interpreted"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as a valid URL."",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if they do enter an invalid URL,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to use the error provider"",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to tell them that they've done that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll set the error against the URL text box,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll give them some kind of message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's see what that looks like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's go into the add podcast form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll enter some invalid data in here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now when we click okay,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we see this flashing error indicator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""When we hover over it, it shows us our error message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now as I've said this is probably overkill for a form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as small as this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But if you had a data entry form with several inputs"",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you could validate all the fields in one go,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and show multiple errors easily using this technique."",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So although that was only a short demonstration"",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of just a few usability techniques,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""hopefully it's given you some ideas"",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for your own applications of how you can make things"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.8858892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just a little bit easier for your end users."",
                          ""displayTime"": 217.8858892
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Localization"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=9&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, let's turn our attention to localization."",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now localizing and translating your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into other languages is quite a large topic,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and worthy if it's own course."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, there is an excellent course on Pluralsight already"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that deals with the whole subject of localization,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and globalization in .NET,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it includes a section on Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So I won't be attempting to cover the whole topic here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but let's just have a look at a few of the things"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that Windows Forms developers will need to bare in mind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when localizing their applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What's actually involved in localizing an application?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, possibly a bit more than you might think at first."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Obviously if you're targeting another language,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll need to translate all the strings into that language."",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But this can raise some interesting issues,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as if you used the mnemonics that we looked at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""earlier in this module, you might need to change those,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because the letters you were using aren't present"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the translated words."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or if you make use of images and icons,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it may be that those are just as appropriate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the target language,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but if your images have any text in them,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then they too may need to be translated as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then there's the layouts of our forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We spent quite a lot of time earlier in this course"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""looking at how we can make our applications resize well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But when you translate into another language,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then the sizes of your labels may need to change."",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Some languages have longer words than others,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""German is quite well know for having longer word lengths."",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or maybe if your translating into a language like Chinese,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you may find you need to use some larger font sizes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""than you were using, so that there's enough vertical space"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the characters to be shown legibly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you're translating into right to left languages,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then there may need to be some quite radical changes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the layout of your forms and controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""One nice trick that Windows Forms has up its sleeve"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to help you with this, is a table layout panel,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which can be told to automatically reverse the order"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of it's columns for right to left languages."",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You also need to take into account"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the different formatting rules that are used"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by different cultures."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Perhaps the most obvious example is date and times."",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""They tend to be formatted and displayed differently"",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""across different cultures."",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The way that dates and times are formatted,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whether it's the day first and then the month,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or the other way around,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is different depending on what culture you're in."",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also, even things like sorting strings,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you want to display strings in alphabetical order,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the order that they get sorted in may depend"",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on what language and culture you're using."",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the way currencies and numbers are displayed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""may also be different."",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as you can see, there's quite a lot of things"",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to take into account when you're localizing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 179.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So what is involved in localizing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your Windows Forms application?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, each of your forms and user controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will already have a default resource file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So for our episode view user control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 194.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's got an EpisodeView.resx file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now what we'll need to do if we want to localize"",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is set the localizable property in the Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""designer to true."",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then, we can choose a language that we want to set"",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the resources for."",
                          ""displayTime"": 213.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So for example, we might set this to French language"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with a Belgian culture."",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then when make changes in the designer,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 220.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms is going to create a new resource file"",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for that culture."",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this resource file will contain only the differences"",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from our base resource."",
                          ""displayTime"": 233.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So it would contain translations probably of all the strings"",
                          ""displayTime"": 235.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but if we didn't any controls about,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 238.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then the locations of the controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 240.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""won't be recorded in this localized resource file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There are other times though,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 246.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the text that you display to the user,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or other resources like images that you display"",
                          ""displayTime"": 250.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the user weren't configured in the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 252.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms designer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 254.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What you need to do in this case is to make use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 257.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of a separate resource file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 259.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Make sure you don't hard code any user visible strings."",
                          ""displayTime"": 261.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now if you have set up your application to be localizable,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 266.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll want to test it out."",
                          ""displayTime"": 268.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you probably don't want to go through the trouble"",
                          ""displayTime"": 271.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of installing a foreign language version of Windows,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 273.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or even changing the culture that your development"",
                          ""displayTime"": 275.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""machine is currently running in."",
                          ""displayTime"": 278.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So there is quite a simple way that you can test out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 280.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your application running against a different culture."",
                          ""displayTime"": 282.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's to change the Thread.CurrentUICulture,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 285.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which specifies which resources are going to be used."",
                          ""displayTime"": 289.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you can also change the Thread.CurrentCulture"",
                          ""displayTime"": 293.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which affects what date formats and string comparsion"",
                          ""displayTime"": 296.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""rules you used."",
                          ""displayTime"": 299.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's see this in action by localizing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 300.5795892
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 303.5795892
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Localization"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=10&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here you can see, I've got our demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I've got the episode view up."",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we look, episode view has already got a resx file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but when we look inside that resx file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's not much in there."",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's because we haven't said that this form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is localizable yet."",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so the Windows Forms designer has been"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""quite happy to hard code the text on all the labels."",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's set this user control to be localizable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now immediately, a load of properties that were being stored"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the auto generated code have now been moved out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the resx file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we can see that it's more than just"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the text and the labels, it's the locations and sizes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and dock and anchoring properties of all the controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because they might change in different languages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and cultures."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now I'm just going to make one very small change here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""since I'm from England, I'd like the word favorite"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be spelt with a u in it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we'll tell the Windows Forms designer"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we're editing the resources for British English."",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So I select English, United Kingdom here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and now I can go to my label,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and update it's text property."",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you'll see that it's created an EpisodeView.en-GB"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""resource file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we look at what's inside there,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ignore the tooltips just for the moment,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll see that really the only thing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's been put in here is our updated string."",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""All the other properties are inherited from the default"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""resource file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's just run that, and check that it works."",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And here we can see, I've got my UK English spelling."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we have a look at what was actually built,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can see that there's this en-GB folder"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our output directory."",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we look inside that, here's a satellite assembly"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""containing only the localized resources for British English."",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this breakdown of resources into their own"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""separate files means that you can ship your product"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""optionally with or without different languages."",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's do something slightly more adventurous,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to now translate this view into French."",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we need to go to the language property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and select French."",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I have to confess that the French I learned at school"",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've mostly forgotten."",
                          ""displayTime"": 155.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we're going to rely on Google Translate,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which of course won't have the necessary context"",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be able to translate these strings properly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Obviously for a real application, you'd pay somebody"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to do a professional job of translating"",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your strings for you."",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so here you can see, I've updated this user control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with the translations that we got from Google Translate."",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you may remember from earlier in this module,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we actually set some strings in the code behind."",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We hard coded some tooltips and a help message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 186.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now this is a practice you'll want to avoid"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're going to be localizing your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 192.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the tooltips we didn't actually need to set here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because the tooltip provider allows us to set them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the designer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Even though there's no tooltip property on a text box,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it appears now, because we have a tooltip control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on our view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 209.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so if we'd set the tooltip values in here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 211.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we'd be able to translate them for French,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and have them appear in our French resx file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 216.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we can at least solve these two,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 221.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but what about this text that's being shown"",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in a message box?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 225.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We haven't got anywhere obvious to put this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the designer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well one thing we can do to get around this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 231.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to create a resx file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 233.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, Windows Forms projects come with a resx file"",
                          ""displayTime"": 235.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""already for you, but there's nothing stopping you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 238.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""creating your own, which we're going to do here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 241.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll add a new resources file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 246.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll call it text resources,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 248.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we can move our string in here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 254.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Each resource has a name, and a value,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 260.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it also has a comment field, which might be useful"",
                          ""displayTime"": 262.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for you to leave notes for the translator"",
                          ""displayTime"": 265.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so they know in what context this string is being used,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which might help them to make a better translation."",
                          ""displayTime"": 270.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""To access that string, we just need to say"",
                          ""displayTime"": 274.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""text resources"",
                          ""displayTime"": 276.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""dot tags help."",
                          ""displayTime"": 280.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But how do we provide a French version of that string?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 282.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well all we have to do is create another resx file"",
                          ""displayTime"": 285.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the French versions of those text resources."",
                          ""displayTime"": 288.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we need to call this file"",
                          ""displayTime"": 293.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""TextResources.fr.resx."",
                          ""displayTime"": 295.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now in here, we can put a translated version"",
                          ""displayTime"": 299.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of that string."",
                          ""displayTime"": 301.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The name has to be the same,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 304.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the value is our translation."",
                          ""displayTime"": 307.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the final thing we need to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 310.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""before we're ready to go,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 312.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to set the culture of our application into French,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 313.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so we can test out that these resources really did work."",
                          ""displayTime"": 316.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And to save time, I've already made those changes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 320.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the startup of the program."",
                          ""displayTime"": 322.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Here we've created a new culture info for French,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 326.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we're setting it to the current UI culture,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 330.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then current culture of the current thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 332.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've also said, that for any new threads that are created,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 336.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as the application progresses, we also want them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 339.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be in French."",
                          ""displayTime"": 342.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's run the application and see if our translation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 345.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""has worked."",
                          ""displayTime"": 348.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And here we can see on the right-hand side,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 350.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""those few labels that we translated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 352.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are now showing in French."",
                          ""displayTime"": 355.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And when we press F1 in the tags text box,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 359.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our help comes up in French."",
                          ""displayTime"": 365.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Obviously we've not quite finished translating"",
                          ""displayTime"": 367.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this application yet, we haven't done the tooltips"",
                          ""displayTime"": 369.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for example."",
                          ""displayTime"": 371.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But hopefully that gives you a good idea"",
                          ""displayTime"": 373.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of what's involved in setting up the resource files"",
                          ""displayTime"": 375.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you need to translate your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 378.9384115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into different languages."",
                          ""displayTime"": 381.9384115
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Summary"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m3&clip=11&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Okay, so we've covered quite a lot of ground"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in this module, but the common thread"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that holds it all together is about being considerate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the needs of our users."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So for our users who are blind or partially sighted,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we looked at how we could improve the accessibility."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For users who want or need to use our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the keyboard only, we looked at how we could do that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For new users to our application, who are using it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the first time and don't already know how to get around,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we looked at how we could improve usability."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And for users who speak other languages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or come from a different culture,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we looked at localization."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's review a few of the best practices"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we applied in our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The first best practice is to make sure you test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your application for accessibility."",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's quite possible that you'll have accidentally"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""broken it with large fonts,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or with high contrast color schemes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we make the recommendation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you might want to set up a virtual machine"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to help you do this kind of testing more easily."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You should also try to make your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""navigable completely from the keyboard,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if that's at all possible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This mean making sure that you've got a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""sensible tab order, and making use of mnemonics,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and other keyboard shortcuts."",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also stressed the importance of helping your users"",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to get it right."",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And usability tests are a great way to discover"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the types of things that your new users"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""might be struggling with."",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We talked about the importance of familiarity,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""building you application with controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that people already know how to use."",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And discoverability, making it very obvious to the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what's expected of them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in our demo application, we showed an example"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of how you might implement help that appears"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the first run of your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how you can add tooltips to controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and how you can provide rich information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the errors that you've made on a data entry from."",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And when we looked at localization,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we focused on the important of resource files."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Getting everything that needs to be translated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into a resx file, whether that's resx files on your forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and user controls, or additional resource files"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you add for strings that are being set"",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the code behind."",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But of course remember, that localization is about"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""more than simply translating resources."",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You do need to bare in mind additional challenges,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as making sure that your date formatting is correct"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the culture you're in, and your string comparisons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""use the appropriate rules for that culture."",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In our next module, we're going to start looking"",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""at some of the best practices for exception handling,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and also how we can run tasks on background threads"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.9515671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our Windows Forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.9515671
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  ""title"": ""Exceptions and Threading"",
                  ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=0&mode=live"",
                  ""clips"": [
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Introduction"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=0&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Hi. My name is Mark Heath, and in this module"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our Windows Forms Best Practices course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we are going to be looking at the subject"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of Exceptions and Threading, and we are going to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""be answering how can I ensure that my application is robust"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the face of various things going wrong, and how can I"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ensure that it's responsive when we've got operations"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are taking a long time to complete."",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll begin by looking at Exceptions, and we will be"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""considering how to handle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""two broad categories of exceptions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, there's what we might call"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Anticipated Exceptions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""These are problems that we know our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""may have to deal with."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, for example, in our My Podcast Demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we've been looking at through this course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when it starts up, we go off to the internet"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we download information about the podcasts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're subscribed to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so it's fairly obvious that we might find, on occasion,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we haven't got network connectivity,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or that we get a 404 Not Found exception,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or even that we download an XML file that we can't parse."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so we should come up with a plan to deal with these type"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of exceptions, they shouldn't take us by surprise."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But of course, there will also sometimes be exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you weren't anticipating."",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Maybe you get a Null Reference exception,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or an Index Out of Bounds exception"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because of a bug in your program."",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so we'll need to have a strategy"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for dealing with these, as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so we'll be addressing the question of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where should we be putting our catch blocks in our code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For anticipated exceptions, you'll most likely"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""be catching them in UI Event Handlers."",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, for example, when you click the Save button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you want to catch any exceptions that happen"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while you're performing a Save operation."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And when we move on to look at threading,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll also want to be catching exceptions that happen"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your non UI threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But we'll also look at how you can add to your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a Global Exception Handler that is going to catch"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of those unanticipated exceptions, and make sure we have"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""at least something that deals with those."",
                          ""displayTime"": 133.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then we'll move on to look at the subject of threading,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll deal with some of the difficult questions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that arise when you're looking to add threading support"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we'll talk about the various options you have"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for actually starting a task on a background thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The .NET framework offers several different ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can do this, and it's quite hard sometimes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to know which one you should be going for."",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we'll discuss the benefits of various options."",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll also look at some of the challenges associated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with dealing with those processes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""running on background threads, such as how can I"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""update the user interface from the background thread,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how can I cancel a running task, how can I avoid re-entrancy"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so that while my background task is running,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the user doesn't start another incidence of the same task,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how do I report the progress"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as the background task is running,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and how do I report when it's completed,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 192.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""either successfully, or with an error."",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I will be updating our demo application to show some ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can do this with Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.0
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Unhandled Exceptions"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=1&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's start by talking about Exceptions,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and in particular, what's going to happen if we don't bother"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to catch any exceptions at all."",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What will it look like to the end user if we just"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""leave all of our exceptions unhandled?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, if those are exceptions coming"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the user interface thread,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for example, you click a button and something goes wrong"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the button click handler, then what the user will see"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is this dialogue here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's not a particularly pretty dialogue."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This comes from the .NET framework,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it allows the user to either continue or quit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And they can click on a Details button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to see the full stack trace."",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you probably don't want a dialogue like this appearing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your application because"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it doesn't look particularly professional."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now if, in your application, you're handling the Paint Event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you're drawing some graphics yourself,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then it will show this message box that we've just seen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But after that, it will just fill in the control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that has had an exception in it's Paint Event Handler"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with this rather ugly looking red X."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so, even if the user chooses to continue,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""now a part of your user interface just looks like this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And again, you don't really want the user seeing that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, what happens if an exception"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in a Windows Forms application occurs"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on a non user interface thread?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You've kicked off a background task,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it throws an exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, in this case, it's even more serious."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You'll see this dialogue, telling you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the application has stopped working, and you have no option"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to continue at all."",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so as you see, it is not a great experience for the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you just leave exceptions unhandled."",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a look at some ways in which we can start"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.8764667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to handle exceptions in our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.8764667
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Global Exception Handlers"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=2&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, we can make a start to handling exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by adding in a Global Exception Handler to our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This will let us catch all of the exceptions that are thrown"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whether on the user interface or in a background thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's have a quick look at how we would do that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, you need to make sure that you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""set the UnhandledExceptionMode to CatchException,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this ensures that the exceptions do go through"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the handler that we're going to create."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we can create our exception handler here, by subscribing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the ThreadException event on the application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This allows us to catch exceptions that have been thrown"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the user interface thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we can give the user the option to continue in this case"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we think that's safe, or if we want to close down"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the application at this point, we can call Application.Exit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you want to catch exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on non user interface threads, then you need"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to handle the unhandled exception event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the current app domain."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, this will allow you to log the exception,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and to show a message to the user."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But what you'll find is it won't give you the option"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to just continue."",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Your application is going to terminate at this point."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so while these Global Exception Handlers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are a good start, they're certainly not the whole solution."",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's look at some more guidelines"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.285989
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for handling exceptions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.285989
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Exception Handling Guidelines"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=3&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, I don't intend in this course"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to go into an exhaustive explanation of how you should"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""be handling exceptions in .NET."",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, if you're interested in that topic,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Deborah Kurata has an excellent course on Pluralsight"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""called \""Defensive Coding in C#\"""",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in which she has a module dedicated to the subject"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of handling exceptions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So what I'm going to do is just highlight"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a few of the principles that Deborah recommends"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in her course, and apply them in a Windows Forms context."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, first of all, don't use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the global exception handler for everything."",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Really, it's only those unanticipated exceptions that should"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""be going through to the global exception handler."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If there are anticipated exceptions, then those should"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""be handled \""locally\"" in time and space."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And by handling them \""locally\"" in time and space,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what we mean is handle it as close to the source"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the exception as possible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Handle it as soon as possible,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as close in the code as possible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You should also, where possible, catch specific exceptions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This allows you to produce meaningful error messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the user, and deal with different type of exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in different ways."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Maybe some exceptions mean that you can retry the operation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it might succeed again, whereas with other exceptions,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's no point in retrying."",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But only catch them if you can actually"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""do something meaningful with them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, one thing that I would recommend"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for those unanticipated exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is make sure you log everything."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Not just the error message, but also the Stack Trace"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the Inner Exception if there is one."",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've made the mistake in the past"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of releasing Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whose global exception handler only shows"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the exception message, and so when an end user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""has reported to me the problem that they've got,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've not had enough information to diagnose"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where it's gone wrong, and so now I make sure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that my error dialogue has got the full to string"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the exception, and has got instructions to my users"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.7080335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for how they can report the error back to me."",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.7080335
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Where to Handle Exceptions"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=4&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, it can sometimes be tricky to decide"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where to put those catch blocks."",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Do you put them in every single function"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your entire application?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, no, that would be too many."",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But here's a few guidelines that you may find useful."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, whenever there's a user initiated action,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for example, the user clicks on a button to do something"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your application, then it's a good idea to wrap the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""business logic method that handles that button click"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and make sure you're catching the anticipated exceptions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you do catch specific anticipated exceptions,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then this allows you to give meaningful error messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the user about what went wrong,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and what they might need to do to correct the problem."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You may find that you also need to perform some cleanup."",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, for example, if you were saving a file"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and halfway through something went wrong,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you might want to delete the half-finished file"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you were writing to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you may need to re-enable buttons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you disabled during the operation,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and so that should be done here, in a finally block."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""However, there will be some events on your user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you probably don't want to handle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in quite the same way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, if you've got a Timer tick, or a Paint event,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or a MouseMove, then you don't want to be"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""showing a message box every time you get an exception"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in one of those, because you could end up with the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""having to click okay on an endless stream of error boxes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if you do catch an exception in an event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that repeatedly fires, then don't just"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""automatically show an error dialogue."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You could maybe show one and keep track of the fact"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you've shown one, or report the error back to the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in some other way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, as we said earlier,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you get an unhandled exception on a background task"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""running on another thread, then it's going to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""take your application down if you don't catch it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So for each background task that you kick off,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you are going to need to make sure that you handle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""any exceptions that happen on that thread if you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""want your application to keep running."",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I will be talking a bit more about that later on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in this module, when we look at threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But if you remember, our demo application hasn't got"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""any exception handling at all at the moment."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So before we start thinking about threads,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""let's go to our demo application and make it more robust"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.383678
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the face of things going wrong."",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.383678
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Global Exception Handler"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=5&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Okay, so here is our demo application again,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and if you remember, the Add button allows us to enter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the feed URL for a new podcast that we want to subscribe to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now also, you may remember from earlier in this course"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we added some protection in this dialogue"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""against the user entering something that's not a URL,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we used an error provider in this instance."",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But what if we enter something that looks like a URL,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but that doesn't exist?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when we click okay, we're actually going to try"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and download a feed from that URL."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as you can see, we get"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this standard unhandled exception message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that allows the user to see more details,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and they can choose whether to continue on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with the application or to quit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, I don't want the users to ever see this dialogue,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so let's start by adding a global exception handler,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then we'll get a bit more specific."",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're going to set up the global exception handler first thing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when we start the application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, let's start off by setting the unhandled exception mode."",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now let's create the exception handler for exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that occur on the user interface thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'll paste in some code here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that does some very rudimentary handling of this exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, we apologize to the user,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we show them the exception message,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and here's where we'd write to a log file if we have one."",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Our demo application doesn't have a log file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but we'd want to get the whole exception to string,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because that will include the Stat Trace"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the Inner Exception, as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And here, I am just going to show the message,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I'm actually going to let the application continue."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as we said earlier,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we wanted to catch exceptions on background threads,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we'd need to do a very similar thing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with the current domain's unhandled exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'd do something similar in here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, we'd log it, and we'd show a message box."",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And remember with this one, the default setting in .NET"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is the application is going to exit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, you can test to see if that's going to happen"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by having a look at the IsTerminating property"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the UnhandledExceptionEventArgs."",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But as I've said, by default, that's going to be true."",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's run our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and see the global exception handler in action."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when we enter the invalid URL,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our custom message dialogue comes up."",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And obviously you'd want to create something"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.4756558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that looks a little bit nicer than this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.4756558
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Handling Anticipated Exceptions"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=6&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you remember we said that we wanted to handle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""anticipated exceptions as locally as possible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We don't want them going through"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the global exception handler."",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this is a great example of an anticipated exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We know that users might be able to enter a URL"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that doesn't exist, so we need to handle that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here, in the event handler, for add subscription,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""after the user has entered the URL, we are calling this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""UpdatePodcast method, and that is the method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that is throwing the exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's put a try-catch around that,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and let's catch WebException, which is the exception we get"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if the URL we enter can't be downloaded."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And one of the advantages of doing this is we can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""give the user an error message that is tailored"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the particular error they've got."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's just check that that works."",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So now when we enter this invalid URL,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we get our custom error message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But that's not the only way this could go wrong."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""They could, for example, type in a valid URL,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but one that isn't a podcast feed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, what if they entered google.com?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, we get a different type of exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's an XML exception, and you can see we've gone back"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""through to our global handler exception again."",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's handle this one as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll add another catch handler for XML exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again, we can show a custom error message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""relating to this particular problem, and maybe give the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""some hints as to what they need to do to fix it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when we enter the URL of a regular webpage"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that is not an XML file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we get our custom error message again."",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But one of the troubles with trying to catch"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the anticipated exceptions, is there tends to be lots"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of different ways in which operations could go wrong."",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, there is another way in which this could fail."",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What if we enter the URL of a valid XML file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as a blog feed, but it's not a podcast feed?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now again we've made it through"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into a global exception handler, and we've got a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""null reference exception because we're looking"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for a node in the XML file that's not there."",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we could of course deal with this situation by adding"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""yet another catch handler for null reference exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But I don't particularly like that solution,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because a null reference exception might mean"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that it's this particular problem, but it might mean"",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that there's a completely unrelated bug, so we need"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be careful about just catching null reference exception"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and assuming we know what it means."",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In this case, it would be better for us to go into"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the update podcast function and to put some checks in here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the nodes we're expecting in the XML really are there."",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If they're not, we could return a false from this function"",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to say that it failed to load,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or we could throw a custom exception"",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that can then be caught specifically when an error message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""tailored to this specific problem"",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""could be shown to the user."",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as you can see, it is a bit of extra work"",
                          ""displayTime"": 197.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're going to handle anticipated exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""specifically, because you have to think through all of the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""possible ways in which your function might fail."",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But if you go to the trouble of doing so,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 209.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then you're going to be able to give the user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 211.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""much more useful error messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 213.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and feedback on how they can fix the problem."",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But that's enough about exceptions for now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 219.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's move on to consider the issue of threading,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 222.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because we still haven't done anything about the fact"",
                          ""displayTime"": 225.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that it might actually take quite a long time"",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to go after the internet and download the information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.6171558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""about all the podcast we're subscribed to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 233.6171558
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Ways to Start a Thread"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=7&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, in .NET, there are actually multiple different ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can start a task on a background thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It can be sometimes quite confusing to know"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which one you ought to be using."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, you can take a delegate and call BeginInvoke on it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""That's called the Asynchronous Programming Model."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can create a Thread object and call Start on it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can use the ThreadPool with QueueUserWorkItem."",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can create a backgroundWorker component"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and call RunWorkerAsync."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can use the new Task Parallel Library and call Task.Run."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you can even use the brand new async and await keywords"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in C# 5, and await an asynchronous function."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, the reason I'm mentioning all of these"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is because this is a Windows Forms course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the likelihood is, if you're using Windows Forms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you may be working on an application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's been around a long time,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so it may well already be using a number"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the older mechanisms for starting threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also, sometimes in Windows Forms applications,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you may find that your customers aren't willing to upgrade"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to newer versions of the .NET framework,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and so options like async and await"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the task parallel library might not be open to you."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now don't worry, I'm not going to try and teach"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how to use all six of these techniques,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but let's just mention a few of the characteristics"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of each one, and then later on we'll be demonstrating"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""one of these in action in our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The Asynchronous Programming Model has been around"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in .NET since near the beginning."",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You kick off a task by calling BeginInvoke on your delegate,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then you don't have to, but you can call EndInvoke,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will get you the results of that delegate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if it returned anything, and also it's there"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can catch any exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that were thrown during the running of that delegate."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""BeginInvoke also returns an IAsyncResult,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this allows you to either wait or poll for completion."",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So this model still works fine,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it can be a bit cumbersome to work with,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 133.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so I wouldn't recommend writing lots of new code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in this style anymore."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The next option is to create and use Thread object"",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and call Start on it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This is actually quite a powerful option,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you can do things like give your thread a name,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is useful for debugging, and even set it's priority."",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Alike with the APM, it allows you to wait"",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or poll for completion."",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But really, creating your own thread"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for every background task is a bit overkill."",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You should be really using the ThreadPool,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so this option is probably only appropriate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you've got a long-running task,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you want to spin up a thread that has a dedicated roll"",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the entire lifetime of your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and maybe you need to set it's priority as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now to kick off a task on the ThreadPool,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you can call ThreadPool.QueueUserWorkItem,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this will either run it immediately,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or if there are no free threads, it will queue it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the next available thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This option doesn't really give you any more help than that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 197.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It won't notify you when your operation is completed,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and if you don't put an exception handler in,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you're going to get the AppDomain unhandled exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Really, this technique has been"",
                          ""displayTime"": 211.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""completely superseded now by the TPL."",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So unless you're not able to use the TPL"",
                          ""displayTime"": 216.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because you're in an earlier version of .NET,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then I wouldn't recommend using this technique at all"",
                          ""displayTime"": 220.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for creating your threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The next option is quite often overlooked,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 228.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it is a very useful component"",
                          ""displayTime"": 231.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's been in the .NET framework for a long time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And it's called the backgroundWorker component."",
                          ""displayTime"": 235.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This is really designed with applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 238.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like Windows Forms in mind."",
                          ""displayTime"": 240.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's got built-in mechanisms to notify us of progress,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 243.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""completion and errors all on the UI thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we don't have to do any work"",
                          ""displayTime"": 250.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to get back onto the UI thread after it's finished."",
                          ""displayTime"": 252.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And it's got a built-in cancellation mechanism,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 255.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is also really useful."",
                          ""displayTime"": 258.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The only potential downside of the backgroundWorker"",
                          ""displayTime"": 261.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that it can encourage you, if you're not disciplined,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 264.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to start putting some of your business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the code behind of your Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 269.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we're going to be discussing in the next module"",
                          ""displayTime"": 272.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""why that's not a very good idea"",
                          ""displayTime"": 275.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from a maintainability perspective."",
                          ""displayTime"": 276.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you're stuck on an older version of the .NET framework,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 279.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this is actually an excellent way to manage tasks"",
                          ""displayTime"": 282.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that need to run on non UI threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 285.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Next, with .NET 4, Microsoft introduced"",
                          ""displayTime"": 290.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Task Parallel Library, which is a very powerful"",
                          ""displayTime"": 292.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and comprehensive framework for dealing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 296.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with all threading-related tasks."",
                          ""displayTime"": 298.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You have the ability to compose tasks,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 301.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to say that when this task is finished,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 303.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this next task should run after it,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 305.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or to run a number of tasks in parallel"",
                          ""displayTime"": 308.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and to wait for them all to complete"",
                          ""displayTime"": 310.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or just for one to complete."",
                          ""displayTime"": 312.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Its also got it's own cancellation token system,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 314.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""allowing you to use a standard way"",
                          ""displayTime"": 317.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to cancel in-progress tasks."",
                          ""displayTime"": 319.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And there's a lot more to it as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 322.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The TPL really is the preferred way"",
                          ""displayTime"": 325.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to do threading now in .NET, and we'll be seeing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 327.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a little bit of it in action in our demo shortly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 330.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, with C# 5 and the .NET 4.5 framework,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 336.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the new async and await C# keywords were introduced."",
                          ""displayTime"": 340.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It is in fact now possible to use these with .NET 4 as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 345.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The async and await keywords aren't really an alternative"",
                          ""displayTime"": 350.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the task parallel library; they build on top of it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 354.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and allow you to write code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 357.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that has a synchronous-looking code flow,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 359.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but is actually running across many different threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 361.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It allows you to do some very cool things,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 365.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like put a try-catch exception handler that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 367.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can catch exceptions that have been thrown on any thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 370.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And another great benefit of this technique,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 374.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're using it with Windows Forms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 376.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that when you await a task from the UI thread,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 379.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when that task finishes, you'll continue on the UI thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 382.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We will see where that's important shortly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 387.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now as I've said, we don't have time in this course"",
                          ""displayTime"": 390.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to go into detail on all of these techniques,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 393.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or even just one of them in any great depth."",
                          ""displayTime"": 395.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But the good news is there's a wealth of training material"",
                          ""displayTime"": 398.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""here on Pluralsight that will help you learn"",
                          ""displayTime"": 401.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""each one of these techniques, whichever one you choose"",
                          ""displayTime"": 404.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to use in your Windows Forms application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 407.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've provided a link here to a post on my blog"",
                          ""displayTime"": 410.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in which I go through each of these six options,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 413.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I provide links to Pluralsight courses"",
                          ""displayTime"": 415.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will give you in-depth training on how to use them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 418.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But before we go to our demo, let's just discuss"",
                          ""displayTime"": 421.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a few more considerations that we need to take into account"",
                          ""displayTime"": 424.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when we're working on background threads"",
                          ""displayTime"": 427.4268558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our Windows Forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 430.4268558
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Updating the User Interface"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=8&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, one of the issues you've almost certainly"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""already run into if you've done any work in Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with background threads is that you can't update"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the user interface from a non UI thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, if you try to do so, you're going to get"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""an InvalidOperationException."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's actually multiple different ways you can solve this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can make use of the BeginInvoke method on a control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this can be on any control that's on your form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if, for example, you run a background thread"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you need to update a label, you can, on that label,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""call BeginInvoke, and then you pass a delegate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that actually does the update."",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you can see here with this cass to action,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the syntax is a little bit cumbersome here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So an alternative that you may prefer"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to make use of the Post method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the SynchronizationContext object."",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What you need to do is on the GUI thread,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""save SynchronizationContext.Current,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then you can use the SynchronizationContext"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you saved to call Post."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again, you pass the delegates of the method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you want to run on the UI thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""An alternative approach is to not try to do any updates"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the user interface from your background thread at all,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and instead, on the user interface, Poll with a Timer"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to find out how things are going on your background thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This may seem a bit of an unsophisticated technique,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but actually it can be quite useful"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when you want your user interface to decide"",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how frequently it's updated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""rather than your background thread process."",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, two of the techniques that we mentioned previously,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using the BackgroundWorker component,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or using the async and await keywords"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""actually provide their own solutions to this problem"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and give you an easy way to get back onto the UI thread"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.051167
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so you can update your controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.051167
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""While a Task Is Running"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=9&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, a few things to bear in mind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while your background task is running."",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, it's often a good idea"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when you've kicked off a background task, to make sure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that any buttons or controls that are going to kick"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that task off again, a second time, are disabled"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to prevent re-entrancy."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And with Windows Forms, you don't actually"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""have to go to every button individually and disable it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can actually disable a container, like a panel"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or a user control, and it will automatically disable"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the child controls it contains."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But it is a good idea to give some indication of progress"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while your task is running."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This may be as simple as just setting the cursor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the WaitCursor, but do remember to make sure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you set it back to the normal cursor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the task is finished."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or if it's a particularly long-running operation,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you may want to show a ProgressBar."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, it's a good idea to offer a cancellation option."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If a background task is taking an extremely long time"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to complete, you're going to want to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""allow the user to cancel it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or if you don't want to provide a cancellation button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a good alternative is to do automatically timeout"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""after a certain duration of time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So that's enough discussion."",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's go back to our demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and let's take the code where we load"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the podcasts when the application starts up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.3956559
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and move that into a background thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.3956559
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Awaiting a Task"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=10&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here we can see the form load event handler"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for our main form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the first thing it does is loads or saves subscriptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from an XML file, or gives us some default subscriptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we're running for the first time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But that's not going to take long to run."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Where we do have some potential for delay is here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as we loop through all subscriptions and call UpdatePodcast,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which goes off to the web"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and downloads the podcast's XML feed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""When that returns, we call AddPodcastToTreeView,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which will add a node to the TreeView for the podcast,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and a child node for each episode."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, we might be tempted to think that we can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""get this full reach loop onto a background thread"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by simply kicking off a new background task"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to load the podcasts."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we could say Task.run"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and pass in an anonymous function like this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But when we run this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we get an argument out of range exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What's going on?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, now we've got code running in the wrong order."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Task.run doesn't block, it just schedules the code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be run on another thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So SelectFirstEpisode is actually getting called"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""before we've loaded in any of our tree nodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's move SelectFirstEpisode inside the anonymous function"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so it doesn't run until after we've loaded all the podcasts."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But now when we run this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we see the invalid operation exception"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we talked about earlier in this module."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're trying to update the TreeView"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the background thread, and that is not allowed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's see how the async and await keywords"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can help us out here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's get the code back to where we started from."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Really, all that we actually need is"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the UpdatePodcast method to run on a background thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""That's the method that's going off and downloading XML files"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the web."",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so, if we look at the code for the UpdatePodcast method,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can see that there's no interaction"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with the user interface in here at all,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so it would be safe to run this on a background thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we'll say that we want to await the return"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the UpdatePodcast function."",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But this gives us a compile error, because UpdatePodcast"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is a void function, so we can't await it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's a couple of ways we can fix this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 155.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but the easy way for now is to use the Task.run method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the task parallel library that we just saw."",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This returns a task, which is what the await keyword needs."",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But we still can't compile because any funtion"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that uses await needs to be marked as async."",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So lets mark this function as async."",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, the difference between awaiting Task.run"",
                          ""displayTime"": 182.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and simply calling Task.run without the await keyword"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that the next line, AddPodcastToTreeView, is not going to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""run until after the UpdatePodcast method has completed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Even better, we're not blocking the UI thread,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and when AddPodcastToTreeView runs,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it will run on the UI thread,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so we won't get an invalid operation exception."",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, before we run this, let's quickly add"",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a short random delay to the UpdatePodcast funtion"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to simulate a slow network."",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, this introduces a random delay of up to three seconds."",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, when we run our application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we see that each of our podcasts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 234.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""gets loaded into the TreeView one by one."",
                          ""displayTime"": 236.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we can even start using the application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 239.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while the other podcasts are still loading."",
                          ""displayTime"": 241.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, the code that auto-selects the first episode"",
                          ""displayTime"": 244.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is now a bit of a nuisance,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""since it could change our selection, so we'd probably"",
                          ""displayTime"": 249.4245004
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""want to address that at some point."",
                          ""displayTime"": 252.4245004
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Demo - Thread Exceptions and Timeouts"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=11&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, before we conclude this demo, I just want to highlight"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a couple more powerful features"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the task parallel library"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and async and await keywords enable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, we can now easily add a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""try-catch exception handler around these two lines."",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The remarkable thing about this is it can catch exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""raised either by the UpdatePodcast method,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or by the AddPodcastToTreeView method,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""even though they are both going to run on different threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So it makes exception handling"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""much more straightforward for you."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Another thing we can now do very easily"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is timeout the loading of each podcast."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'll remove this exception handling code for now,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll save the return value of Task.run"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into a local variable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, instead of awaiting this task, I'm going to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""wait for the first of two tasks to complete,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using Task.WhenAny."",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This function returns a task that completes as soon as"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the first of the tasks you pass it have completed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we'll race our UpdatePodcast task against a simple task"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that delays two seconds, and see which one wins."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If the first task to complete is our UpdatePodcast task,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that means we didn't timeout,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so we can add it into the TreeView."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if it's the delay task, that means we've timed out,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and so we'd run any code that we have to deal with timeouts."",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, since we put a random delay of up to three seconds"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into our UpdatePodcast function,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we should get a couple of timeouts."",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's load our application, and see how many"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the four podcasts we've subscribed to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""manage to load in under two seconds."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And here we can see three of them managed to load,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the fourth one timed out."",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So hopefully this short demo has illustrated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just how straightforward it is to get started"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using the async and await keywords to introduce threading"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.4492671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into your Windows Forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.4492671
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Summary"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m4&clip=12&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, let's review what we've learned in this module."",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've looked at how to deal with exceptions,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and how to work with threads"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in your Windows Forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the goals we have in mind are"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for robustness in the face of things going wrong,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and for responsiveness in the face of things"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""taking a long time to complete."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Once again, we put into practice the things that we learned"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by making some updates to our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Here's a few of the best practices that we looked at."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First, remember to handle anticipated exceptions \""locally.\"""",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""That is, if you know a specific exception is going to occur,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then you catch that specific exception as close as possible"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to where it was raised, and that allows you to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""report back to the user with a meaningful error message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You also need to remember to clean up any operations"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that were aborted halfway through."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You should also, however, provide a global exception handler"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for those exceptions that you can't anticipate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you don't really know what to do with."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In these cases, it is important that you remember"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to log everything so that you can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""troubleshoot the problem later."",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you may wish to exit the application at this point"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in case it's gone into a corrupted state."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you do have long-running tasks in your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then these need to be performed in background threads."",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we saw how the Task Parallel Library,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in conjunction with the async and await keywords,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""really make it very easy to work"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with threads in Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, we discussed why you need to make sure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you always update the user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the user interface thread."",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we saw how, if you await long-running tasks"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using the await keyword, then that's going to make your life"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""much easier, because you'll already be back on the UI thread"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the await is completed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In our next module, we are going to be looking"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""at techniques you can use to make sure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.1930338
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that your code is maintainable and testable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.1930338
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  ""title"": ""Patterns for Maintainable Code"",
                  ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=0&mode=live"",
                  ""clips"": [
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Introduction"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=0&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Hi, my name's Mark Heath."",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in this module of our Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Best Practices course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to be looking at various patterns"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will help us to maximize the maintainability"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now you may be wondering"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how is writing maintainable Windows Forms code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""any different to writing maintainable WPF code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or maintainable websites?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in one sense, Windows Forms is no different"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to other types of application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The same principles and techniques that you would use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to make sure that your WPF or website applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""were maintainable"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can on the whole be applied to Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But the reason I want to specifically address"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""maintainability in this course on Windows Forms development"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that there's a style of coding"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that Windows Forms applications often follow."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And it's one that can really start to hinder your progress"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as you application gets larger."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this style of coding"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that I want to encourage you to avoid"",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is where all the code for your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ends up living in event handlers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the code behind of your MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Because it's so easy just to drag controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""onto a form using the Designer in Visual Studio,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and attach event handlers to those controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's not uncommon for Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to contain form classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that have hundreds of controls on them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and have thousands of lines of code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in their code behind."",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we've seen this in the demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we've been working on throughout this course."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Currently, the vast majority of the code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is in mainform.cs."",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's a monolithic mainform."",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""All of the code to load and save our subscriptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is in there,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the code to go off to the internet"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and download new episodes is in there"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and all of the code to edit and play podcasts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is in there."",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as our application grows larger and larger,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and gains more and more features,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this class is only going to get larger."",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But why is this a problem?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So what if our MainForm has got"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""5,000 lines of code in it?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, here's why this'll cause you problems."",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, that much code is simply hard"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to comprehend."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's hard to reason about what impact"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the changes you make will have,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because there's so much to take in."",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so this'll inevitably slow down future development."",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Second, it's extremely difficult to perform"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""any kind of automated testing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""since the only way to exercise the business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is through the user interface."",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So applications built in this style"",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""often only end up getting tested manually,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as a result"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the percentage of test coverage is very low."",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And third, if your business logic is intertwined"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with the user interface code on your form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then it becomes almost impossible to reuse it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this tends to lead to the cut and paste"",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""coding antipattern,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where you simply introduce another copy"",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of existing code and modify it,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""rather than extracting common functionality out."",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the ability to reuse code is also very important"",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you plan to migrate away from Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to a newer user interface technology,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as WPF, or maybe a HTML5 website."",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Even though you'll be rewriting a presentation layer,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll still want to be able to reuse the business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 205.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you can't do that if it's tightly coupled"",
                          ""displayTime"": 209.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to your Windows Forms controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So in this module, we'll consider some practical ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 216.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can avoid creating these monolithic forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 219.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which are so hard to maintain, test and reuse."",
                          ""displayTime"": 222.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll start by briefly discussing a technique"",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we've actually already seen in action"",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""earlier in this course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's segregating your user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 234.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by creating custom user controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 236.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then we'll talk about the importance"",
                          ""displayTime"": 240.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of extracting business logic out of behind of your forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 241.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll look at a technique where you create passive Views,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 248.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which are controlled by Presenters,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 251.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this is a pattern known as Model View Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 254.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll also see how the Command pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 258.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can be really useful,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 260.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""particularly for dealing with the buttons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 262.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on your user interface."",
                          ""displayTime"": 264.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally we'll discuss the Event Aggregator pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 266.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which allows different parts of our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 269.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to send messages easily to each other,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 272.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and greatly reduces coupling."",
                          ""displayTime"": 274.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll be briefly demonstrating"",
                          ""displayTime"": 278.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""each of these techniques,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 279.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by applying them to our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 281.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's get started."",
                          ""displayTime"": 283.5
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Segregate Your User Interface"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=1&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now if you've been following throughout this course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll remember that when we looked"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""at resizing and tab order,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we found that it was much easier to implement"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""those features"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we took some of the controls off the MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and moved them into their own user controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you may also remember"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that while it was easy enough to move the controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""their code behind wasn't nearly so easy"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to extract out,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we opted for a rather unpleasant solution,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where we simply made the private control member variables"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the user control public, just so our MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""could still access them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so while it helped us with the tab order and resizing,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we didn't address the growing maintainability issue"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we had in our MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And for this reason, I strongly recommend segregating"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your user interface into user controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""right from the outset."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Because although it's not impossible,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's quite difficult to do retrospectively."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so once a form starts to get bloated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with dozens of user controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it becomes extremely hard to stop it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""continuing to grow."",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""As an example, let's look again at the MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've added a toolbar to it since the last module"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as it will help us to illustrate some of the techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll be talking about in this module."",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""As you can see here, there are three obvious candidates"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for separate components, or Views."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's the toolbar, which we could call the Toolbar View,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's the Tree View on the left,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which we called the Subscriptions View,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then, on the right hand panel,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we had two things that could go in there,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there was the Episode VIew, which is what you can see now,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and there was also the Podcast View,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when you selected a Podcast tree node on the left."",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so the MainForm of our application as it stands"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is composed out of four Views."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact you can see here, looking at the Episode View,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that even that could potentially be split into two parts,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""one static part that just gives us information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""about the episode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then the part at the bottom,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which allows us to edit our tags and notes and ratings"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the episode."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we were to separate those out into two views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it would give us the flexibility in the future"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to switch to different layouts easily,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as a tab layout,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where the details are in one tab, and the editing controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""were in another tab."",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So this technique of segregating your user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into smaller user controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you can think of as applying the single responsibility"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""principle to user interfaces."",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're simply segregating the controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into logical groups that share a common purpose"",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it allows us to compose our MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.3512
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of a small number of simple user controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.3512
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Extract Business Logic From Code Behind"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=2&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But segregating our controls into their own user controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or Views is only the first step."",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Next we need to get the business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of the code behind of our user interface components."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we need to start by identifying the code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that doesn't belong in there"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then we need to extract it out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into one or more classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""each with a single responsibility."",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's see if we can do that with our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're looking at our MainForm class here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and currently there's almost 300 lines of code in here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's only going to grow,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as pretty much every feature in our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""results in more code being added to this class."",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So what can we remove from here?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, first, the code we can see here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""loads our list of podcast subscriptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""along with all the notes and ratings we've made"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from an XML file."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And here, we have the code that saves it back to XML"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when we exit the application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Really this code doesn't belong"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the user interface layer at all."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we could create a SubscriptionManager class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and move this logic into it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then here's the code to update our podcast"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which goes off to the internet"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to see if it can find new episodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This code would really benefit"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from some good unit test coverage,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as we'll likely have to deal with"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""various kinds of issues,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as different formats of the XML structure."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's get this code out as well, into its own class,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we'll call it the PodcastLoader class."",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And another thing that's in our MainForm,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is some code to play back the podcast episodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Currently all we can do is play, pause and stop,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it's not hard to imagine that soon we'll also be wanting"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to set the volume level and reposition within the fille."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So the audio playback functionality also ought to get"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""refactored out into its own class."",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we could call that the PodcastPlayer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now to save time, I'm not going to make you watch"",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while I extract out each of these three classes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but you can see the finished work here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've got the SubscriptionManager"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is handling reading and writing to our XML file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and can load the podcasts we subscribe to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and save the podcasts we subscribe to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then we've got PodcastLoader"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which as you can see, still retains the ability"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to work asynchronously,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as we said earlier, this is a class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we really want to get under unit test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and now we're not too far off being able to do that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we've got our PodcastPlayer class here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which moves the audio playback code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of our MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so if we now have a look at what impact this has"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on our MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the total number of lines in this class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 175.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""has dropped by about 100"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you and can see here in the Constructor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 179.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're constructing an instance"",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of each of these business logic classes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Obviously the next step to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 185.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""would be to inject those as dependencies"",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but we won't do that just yet,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as we've got further improvements to make first."",
                          ""displayTime"": 192.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the good thing is now in our MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as we look down, virtually all of the code in here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is interacting with the user interface controls in some way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've managed to get a large chunk of business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of the way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But we're not done yet."",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We can simplify this further,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 213.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using the Model View Presenter pattern."",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so the next thing we need to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 217.6999556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to create view interfaces."",
                          ""displayTime"": 219.6999556
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""More Business Logic to Extract"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=3&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now although what we just saw"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""was a big step in the right direction"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in getting a lot of the obviously non user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""related code out of the code behind for the MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there still is actually some business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""hiding away inside MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the giveaway is some of these If statements"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can see here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In this method, we're making a decision"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on what we're going to show on the right-hand panel"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""depending on what's been selected in the left-hand panel,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and really that's a business logic decision."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We should be able to unit test that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so it shouldn't be living inside the user interface."",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Likewise here, when we're going off to the internet"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and trying to update a podcast."",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're handling a couple of anticipated exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and deciding that when these two particular problems"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are encountered,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we should show specific error messages."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again, that's really a business logic decision"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we ought to be able to unit test that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But we can't because it's in the code behind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for our MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's think now about how the Model View Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""pattern can help us get all of our business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.2558779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of our Views and into unit testable Presenter classes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.2558779
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""The Model View Presenter Pattern"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=4&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So what is the Model View Presenter pattern?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, what's referred to by the Model"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is our business entity objects."",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In our demo application, this is going to be the Podcast"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the Episode class,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and also those business logic classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are able to save and load our business entities."",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then we have our Views."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And these are our forms and our user controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the important thing in Model View Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is we're trying to prevent the View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from directly manipulating the Model."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The View is not allowed to go off to the business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and start making calls into it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Instead, the View in Model View Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is supposed to be entirely passive."",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so it's the job of the Presenter to tell the View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what it should be displaying."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So the Presenter is allowed to go off to the Model"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""get some data and then tell the View to display that data."",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The View doesn't make any decisions,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it just displays the data it's been told to display."",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then, if the user makes any interactions in the View,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""say they click on a button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or maybe they select a different node in the tree view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""again the View doesn't make any decisions at all,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it just passes on the information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""back to the Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The Presenter can decide what to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in response to that button click"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then it can update the View again"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with any changes that resulted"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from that user interaction."",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so as you can see from this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we implement Model View Presenter correctly,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our View classes, our forms and user controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are going to become very simple."",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""They're just going to provide ways for the Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to get and set data, and to report back"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what user interactions have taken place."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's see how this would look"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.9334335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we created some View interfaces on our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.9334335
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Creating View Interfaces"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=5&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's start by looking at the simplest View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our demo application, and that's the Podcast View."",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The only thing that this View does"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is shows us two bits of information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""about the selected podcast:"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""its title, and how many episodes there are."",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so we could make a View interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that just has this set Podcast method on it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Although that would be a little bit naughty"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in terms of MVP, because we're passing our Model"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""directly to our View,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and so that would allow the View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to sneakily update the Model, which it's not supposed to do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So maybe it would be better to do something like this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""have a Set Podcast Title method,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and a Set Episode Count method."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as you can see, the View is trivially simple"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to implement."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It doesn't even get to format the string"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for Episode Count,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it just displays the data it's been given by the Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's consider a slightly more complicated View."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The Subscription View, which if you remember"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is the tree view on the left-hand side"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which displays all the podcasts and their episodes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and allows the user to select which one"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they want to look at."",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now in this View we need to be able to tell it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to add nodes to the tree, and remove them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We need to be able to tell it which nodes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""should be selected,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and if the user changes the selection,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we need to be notified, and to be able to find out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which node they selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as you can see here, I've created a very simple"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ISubscriptionView view interface that lets us do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""each of those five things."",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if we look at the implementation for SubscriptionView"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can see its extremely straightforward."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's no conditional logic in there at all."",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, SubscriptionView has no idea what it's displaying"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it doesn't know that it's displaying podcasts and episodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's just showing the nodes it's been told to show."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so again, we've achieved our aim"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of moving all of the business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of the View and into the Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Next up is the EpisodeView, and in this View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we need to be able to set the description, title,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and publication date of the episode we're looking at,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and there are also some fields that users can edit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we've got getters and setters"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the ratings, notes and tags."",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We don't actually need to raise events at the moment"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the user enters the data"",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because the Presenter only needs to examine"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this information when you move away from the episode"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you're currently looking at."",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again, if we look at the implementation of EpisodeView"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll see it's trivially simple,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all we're doing is getting and setting properties"",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the various controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's no conditional logic in here at all."",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Okay, so we're nearly done now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's just quickly look at the ToolbarView,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as you can see here we've got a user control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that simply contains a Windows Forms toolstrip"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's got our buttons on it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 186.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And what does the view interface that we need"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for this View look like?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, it just really needs to tell us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the user clicked on the various buttons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The only special case in this View,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is that one of the buttons changes its icon"",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""depending on whether the episode has been marked"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as a Favorite or not."",
                          ""displayTime"": 205.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if we look up at the implementation of this View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 208.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""again you can see it's very trivial."",
                          ""displayTime"": 211.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're just passing along the click events"",
                          ""displayTime"": 213.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the buttons on the toolbar."",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, we can consider the MainFormView."",
                          ""displayTime"": 219.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's built up out of the four smaller Views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 222.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we just looked at."",
                          ""displayTime"": 224.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It does need a few other events if we're to get"",
                          ""displayTime"": 226.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the logic that was in the code behind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 228.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of MainForm out."",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We need to identify when the form was loaded and closed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and when hotkeys have been pressed,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 235.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or help has been requested."",
                          ""displayTime"": 237.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we also need to be able to say"",
                          ""displayTime"": 239.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which of the two Views should be showing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 240.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the right-hand panel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now if we look at the code for MainForm,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 245.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you can see it's trivially simple."",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It fits here just on one screen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 249.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""All it's doing is putting the appropriate views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 252.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into the right parts of our split container."",
                          ""displayTime"": 254.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we've created all our View interfaces,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 258.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the implementations of those interfaces"",
                          ""displayTime"": 260.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are really quite trivial."",
                          ""displayTime"": 263.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's run the application and see what happens."",
                          ""displayTime"": 264.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as you can see, our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 269.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""doesn't seem to be working."",
                          ""displayTime"": 271.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""No podcasts are displayed on the left,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 273.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""nothing's shown on the right-hand side,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 275.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and none of the buttons on the toolbar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 278.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""do anything when we click them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 280.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's because we've not wired up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 283.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our Presenter yet."",
                          ""displayTime"": 284.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This is just a completely passive View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 286.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that doesn't do anything."",
                          ""displayTime"": 288.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a look at the Presenter,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 290.2144335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and connect it up to our MainFormView."",
                          ""displayTime"": 292.2144335
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Connecting the Presenter"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=6&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here you can see our MainForm Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And really all that's in this class is all the code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that used to be in the code behind of MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The only difference is, is that rather than being able"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to access the user interface components directly,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we have to access them through their View interfaces."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's wire up the Presenter to the MainForm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and check it works,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then we'll come back and look at this Presenter,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and point out a few ways in which"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we could improve things further."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So when our application starts up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we create the MainForm,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but now we also need to create the Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will control the MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's all we have to do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when we run the application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can see everything's working again."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We can select episodes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and play them, or mark them as Favorites."",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we said there were a few problems"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with our MainForm Presenter,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so let's go and have a look at the code again"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and point out what those are."",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, even though we created four or five Views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we've just got one Presenter,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it means this Presenter is quite long and bloated."",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Ideally, we'd create a Presenter to go with each View."",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again, following the single responsibility principle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but this time with our Presenters,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""instead of our Views."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But the other glaring problem with this MainForm Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as it currently stands is that we still can't unit test it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's because we're creating these classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we depend on here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which are actually going to interact with files on the disk,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or go off to the network,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or play sound on our sound card."",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And also if we look further down here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll see we're dong things like showing message boxes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and making changes to our application's settings."",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So really, if we want to be able to unit test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our Presenter, which was one of the goals"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for getting the code out of the code behind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of MainForm in the first place,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to need to inject dependencies"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into our MainForm Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.0918891
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a quick look at what that would look like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.0918891
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Refactoring the MainForm Presenter"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=7&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now once again, I'm not going to make you watch"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while I refactor all of the dependencies"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of MainForm Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But what you can see here is the results of doing so."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Those three business logic classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we were previously creating in the Constructor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are now injected via interfaces."",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this means that we can mock them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for unit testing purposes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if we look at the SubscriptionManager for example,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll see that we've just extracted the public methods"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of that existing class into an interface."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you'll also see that I've got four other"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""dependencies that I've introduced as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this helps us to completely eliminate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the untestable code from MainForm Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The message box display service"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""has an implementation that actually shows"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a message box,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Settings service is able to save changes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to our Application Settings file,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the System Information service simply tells us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we're in a high contrast color scheme or not,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the new Subscription service pops up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the new podcast dialog"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and tells us what URL was entered."",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so as you can see, those are extremely simple services"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but what they do is they mean that now, finally,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we've got to the place we wanted to get to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""All the business logic in MainForm Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is completely unit testable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's just see what changes, though,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this makes to our application startup"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when we create the MainForm Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""As you can see here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's quite a bit more setup work involved."",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've got to make all of those dependencies"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then pass them into the Constructor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of MainForm Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if you're thinking this looks a little bit cumbersome,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you're right, it is."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this is exactly the type of issue"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that Inversion of Control containers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are designed to address."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so you could make use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of an Inversion of Control container"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like StructureMap or Ninject here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it would be able to automatically construct"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your MainForm Presenter for you,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""supplying all of its dependencies."",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now as I've said, we've still got quite a lot of code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in MainForm Presenter, because it's actually managing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of our Views,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and so we might want to refactor this further"",
                          ""displayTime"": 133.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to use individual Presenters for each View."",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But we're not going to do that here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Instead, I want to show you another pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will help simplify things further"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.2536114
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's the Command pattern."",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.2536114
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""The Command Pattern"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=8&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a look at what the Command pattern is"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and why we might want to use it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Really, all that the Command pattern involves"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is creating a class for each command in your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so in our demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this would be a command for each of those buttons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the toolbar."",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as an example, consider the Play button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which allows you to play the selected podcast."",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'd create a class called PlayCommand."",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this class would have a method called Execute."",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And when the user clicks the Play button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Execute method on the Play Command object"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will be called."",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Having a class for each command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is going to help unclutter our Presenter classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it also allows us to store"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a lot of related information about each command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""along with it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""A very common example is for each command object"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to have an IsEnabled property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that says whether the button on the toolbar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""should be enabled or not."",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And it would need to raise an event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to indicate that that state had changed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you can take it further than this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You might also have an IsVisible property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if some commands need to disappear"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""off the toolbar under certain circumstances."",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Since our commands are all stored on a toolbar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we could even put an Icon property"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on our command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which will allow us to change the icon that's displayed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while the application's running,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which we need to do for our Favorite button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We could also store the ToolTip for the command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the ShortcutKey that triggers it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Quite often as well, when you're using the Command pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll make a Base class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from which all of your command objects inherit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this can handle certain common behavior"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and keep it out of the way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""A good example would be exception handling."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You could catch any unanticipated exceptions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the PlayCommand's Execute method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and handle them in a consistent way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In your application as well, you may need to check"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the privileges and licensing of the current user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""before they're allowed to execute a command."",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so this potentially duplicated code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can be pushed into the Base class."",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the Base class could do other things,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for example, like protecting us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from executing the command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while IsEnabled is set to False."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's see what difference using the Command pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.9957448
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""makes to our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.9957448
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Implementing the Command Pattern"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=9&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now once again, I'm not going to make you watch me"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""implement this pattern."",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the reason for that is,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like with many of the other techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we've been looking at, it takes quite a bit of time"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to retrofit it to an existing application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You'll always find it easiest"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to implement patterns like this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you start your application using them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But I'll show you what I've done here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's really not that complicated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so you should be able to follow along."",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I started by creating a Toolbar command interface,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which each of the buttons on our toolbar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is going to implement."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've got the Execute method that we just talked about"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the IsEnabled property that will allow us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to dynamically enable and disable buttons."",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've also given our commands the ability"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to set their Icons, ToolTips and specify"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what ShortcutKey launches them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'm also making use of an interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that if you're a WPF programmer you'll be familiar with"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's the INotifyPropertyChanged"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's through this interface that our Toolbar commands"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are going to be able to report to the View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that some of their properties, like IsEnabled"",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or Icon, have changed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which will allow the View to update the buttons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the toolbar."",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as we discussed, we've also made a Base class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that all of our command objects will inherit from,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's CommandBase."",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in this simple implementation,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""really all it's doing is raising the PropertyChanged"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""notifications when we modify IsEnabled or Icon, for example."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What this means is, people inheriting CommandBase"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just need to override the Execute method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and set up the Icon and ToolTip"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that they want to be displayed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a look at an example command implementation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll look at the Play command."",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as you can see here, it's really simple."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We just set up the Icon and ToolTip,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the ShortcutKey we want to use,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then when the Execute method is called"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we call Play on the PodcastPlayer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you can see our Play command object"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""takes the PodcastPlayer as a dependency."",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What does this pattern mean for the Toolbar View?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's go and have a look at that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well the Toolbar View interface has now become"",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""trivially simple."",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's just got one method on, SetCommands,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and passes in an array of toolbar commands."",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we look at the implementation of that method"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our Toolbar View, all we do is we clear out any buttons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""already in the toolstrip, and for each command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we create a new toolstrip button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""set up its properties, and also make sure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we're listening to the PropertyChanged event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so that we can change the text, image"",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and Enabled state of the button to reflect the changes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that have been made in the Command object."",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also need to subscribe to the Click event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so we can call the Execute method on the command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 179.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that this button is associated with."",
                          ""displayTime"": 182.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you'll notice now that the Toolbar View"",
                          ""displayTime"": 186.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""doesn't know or care what the commands"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in its toolbar are actually for."",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It just displays whatever commands it's given."",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And even though we have got a For-Each loop here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll still see there's no conditional logic in here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""no business decisions are being made"",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the Toolbar View."",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the final thing we need to look at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is how this is all set up in the first place."",
                          ""displayTime"": 208.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this happens at startup."",
                          ""displayTime"": 213.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We need to create an instance"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of each of the command objects that we've created"",
                          ""displayTime"": 216.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for all the commands on our toolbar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 219.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as you can see we've got seven of these commands"",
                          ""displayTime"": 221.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and some of them take quite a large number"",
                          ""displayTime"": 224.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of dependencies."",
                          ""displayTime"": 225.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So again, this is a situation where if we had"",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""an Inversion of Control container,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it would make creating all of these command objects"",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""much easier for us."",
                          ""displayTime"": 234.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now what was the benefit of doing this?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 237.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, what we've ended up with is each command"",
                          ""displayTime"": 239.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""isolated into its own class,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is completely unit testable"",
                          ""displayTime"": 244.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's also prevented our MainForm Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from getting bloated with all the code to handle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 250.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all the buttons that are currently on the toolbar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 252.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and future ones."",
                          ""displayTime"": 255.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So this Command pattern is a really great one"",
                          ""displayTime"": 257.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 259.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you've got lots of commands"",
                          ""displayTime"": 261.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you want to stop your classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 263.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""getting really large with loads of button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 264.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ClickHandler methods."",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's move on now to look at the final technique"",
                          ""displayTime"": 269.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we'll cover in this module,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 271.804456
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is the use of an Event Aggregator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 273.804456
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Event Aggregators"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=10&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In the lifetime of a Windows Forms application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there are going to be events that happen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'm not just talking about the events"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are on controls, like button clicks,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but anything that happens in your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that some other part of the code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""might be interested in responding to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in some way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so there'll be some classes that we can think of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as Event Publishers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and others as Subscribers."",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""A Publisher knows when something happens."",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And a Subscriber knows what to do when that thing happens."",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So they need to communicate in some way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now there's two ways that you could do this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can hard code into the Publisher,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the knowledge of who the Subscriber is."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So the Publisher says when it happens,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I know who to call."",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And it makes a call directly to the Subscriber class."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In this case, the dependency goes from the Publisher"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the Subscriber."",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now this is fine, but the trouble happens"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when we have multiple Subscribers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""who are all interested in being notified"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the event happens."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It means that the Publisher now needs to depend on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""every Subscriber."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's not particularly easy to sustain."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so the solution to this would be to invert"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that dependency, and for the Publisher to raise"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a regular .NET event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This allows one or more Subscribers to go to the Publisher"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and register their interest in that event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So the dependency works the other way 'round now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now this does improve things"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you've got multiple Subscribers."",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Of course, it doesn't help you much"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if there are multiple Publishers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because then the Subscribers must now go"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and subscribe to all the Publishers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the same event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But what you can see here is that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whichever way 'round we do it,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there is a dependency going between these two classes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's see what the Event Aggregator offers us."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""When you're using an Event Aggregator,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the Publisher decides that something's happened"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the rest of the system needs to know about,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it sends a message to the Event Aggregator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then the Event Aggregator's job"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to pass that mesage along to any other parts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the system that are interested."",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so now this means the Subscribers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""don't connect directly to the Publishers,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or the Publishers directly to the Subscribers."",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The Subscriber simply asks the Event Aggregator"",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to tell them when the message that they're interested in"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""happens."",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so what this means is that everyone"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""depends on the Event Aggregator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But this can actually simplify things considerably."",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Often the Event Aggregator is implemented"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as a singleton;"",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""one Event Aggregator for the entire application to use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to pass messages around."",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so let's look now at our demo application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and see an example of how using an Event Aggregator"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is going to save us passing around"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""loads of dependencies all over the place,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.2129783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""particularly in our command objects."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.2129783
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Using an Event Aggregator"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=11&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""One of the events in our demo applcation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that lots of parts of the code are interested"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in handling is what happens"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when you select a different node in the Tree View."",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's select an episode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and when we did that, the Main View needed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to know about it, so it could tell"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the right-hand panel to show the Episode View."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The Episode View itself needed to know about it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because it wanted to update all of its labels"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and text boxes to show information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""about the selected episode."",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And also the Toolbar View needed to know about it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so that it could disable buttons,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or set the icon on the Favorite button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if this episode had been marked as a Favorite."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in fact, also the PodcastPlayer class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is interested in this event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because if you're currently playing an episode"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you navigate away to a different one"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then the episode that you were playing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""needs to stop playing."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so the Event Aggregator in this case"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""would be really useful if we could publish a message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""saying, an episode has been selected,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or a podcast has been selected,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you click on one of the higher level tree nodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then all of the parts of the application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are interested in responding in some way"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to an episode becoming selected"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""only need to request that information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the Event Aggregator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a look at how that can be implemented."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's start off by looking at the Event Aggregator"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""class itself."",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now basically it's only got two methods"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we really care about for this example."",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can ask the Event Aggregator to publish"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a message for you,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you can tell the Event Aggregator that you're interested"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in subscribing to a message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and give it an action you want it to call you back on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when that message is published."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This Event Aggregator also allows you to unsubscribe."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we've also said for all of the messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we pass around through the Event Aggregator"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are going to inherit from a marker interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""called Application Event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You don't have to do this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it does make it easier to find"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all the possible events that could be sent"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""through the Event Aggregator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Don't worry too much about the implementation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we're using,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's plenty of open source Event Aggregators"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can just make use of."",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But this one is implemented as a singleton."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So it's going to be extremely simple"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for anywhere in our code to publish messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 142.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the Event Aggregator"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or to subscribe to them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's add two messages or application events"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we're going to be publishing."",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The first is for when an episode has been selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It will inherit from ApplicationEvent"",
                          ""displayTime"": 158.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as a property, it will have the episode"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that was actually selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this is a good practice."",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You should always include in your messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the information that the Subscriber will need"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in order to handle it properly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's also make a podcast selected message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 175.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for it the user clicks on a podcast tree node."",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So that's our events set up, now let's publish them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the user selects a different tree node."",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now because we haven't made a Presenter class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 191.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the Subscription View yet"",
                          ""displayTime"": 194.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll have to do this from the MainForm Presenter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Here's the current code that's dealing with"",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the selected tree node gets changed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as you can see, it's already calling"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into lots of different places."",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This MainForm Presenter is trying to keep track"",
                          ""displayTime"": 208.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of all the bits of code that are interested"",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in this particular event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So actually there's great potential for us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to simplify this by using an Event Aggregator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 216.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if the selected tree node was an episode"",
                          ""displayTime"": 220.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""let's publish the Episode Selected message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the message parameter will be the episode"",
                          ""displayTime"": 227.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that was selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if it was a podcast, let's publish"",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a podcast selected message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 235.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""As you can see that was quite straightforward."",
                          ""displayTime"": 239.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you're worried that this might hamper"",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our ability to unit test,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 244.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""actually it doesn't at all."",
                          ""displayTime"": 246.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Event Aggregators are very unit test friendly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""All we'd need to do on our unit test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 250.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is subscribe on the Event Aggregator to that message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 252.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and just check that it really was published"",
                          ""displayTime"": 255.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when we expected it to be."",
                          ""displayTime"": 257.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's go and subscribe to our messages."",
                          ""displayTime"": 260.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'd like the Play button in our toolbar"",
                          ""displayTime"": 265.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""only to be enabled when an episode is selected"",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and not when a podcast is selected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 271.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we'll start with the button disabled,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 273.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then we'll subscribe to EpisodeSelected."",
                          ""displayTime"": 277.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll do that by getting a reference"",
                          ""displayTime"": 280.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the Event Aggregator singleton"",
                          ""displayTime"": 282.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and telling it we're interested in subscribing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 284.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to Episodeselectedmessages."",
                          ""displayTime"": 287.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then we'll give it this lambda function"",
                          ""displayTime"": 290.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to set our IsEnabled property to True."",
                          ""displayTime"": 292.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""At the moment we don't need to examine"",
                          ""displayTime"": 296.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the episode message itself to determine if"",
                          ""displayTime"": 298.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can enable the button,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 300.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but in the future we might need to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 302.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so it's useful that we've got it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 303.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll do the same thing for the Podcastselectedmessage"",
                          ""displayTime"": 306.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and disable the Play command."",
                          ""displayTime"": 309.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's just test this and check that it works"",
                          ""displayTime"": 312.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you can see here, we've started out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 316.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with the Play button disabled."",
                          ""displayTime"": 317.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we select different podcast nodes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 320.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're getting the Podcastselectedmessage"",
                          ""displayTime"": 323.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and Play button stays disabled."",
                          ""displayTime"": 325.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But if we select an episode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 328.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we get the Episodeselectedmessage,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 330.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it allows our Play button to become enabled."",
                          ""displayTime"": 332.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again the Subscribers are easy to unit test as well"",
                          ""displayTime"": 337.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because all you'd need to do is create an instance"",
                          ""displayTime"": 341.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the Play command, and then publish these messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 343.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the Event Aggregator, and check"",
                          ""displayTime"": 346.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the EnabledState changes appropriately."",
                          ""displayTime"": 348.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And hopefully you can see from this very short demo"",
                          ""displayTime"": 351.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we could now very easily go into all the other parts"",
                          ""displayTime"": 354.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 356.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are interested in responding to this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 357.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""selected episode or podcast changing,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 359.9641783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and subscribe to these messages on the Event Aggregator."",
                          ""displayTime"": 362.9641783
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Summary"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m5&clip=12&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's just review what we've learned in this module."",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've looked at several different techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will help you to write maintainable"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and testable Windows Forms code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We started with looking at segregating"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your user interface into user controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""rather than just putting all of your controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""onto your MainForm."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then we looked at identifying business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that has nothing to do with the user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's currently in the code behind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and how we could get it out into its own classes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then we moved on to the Model View Presenter pattern."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we talked about creating passive Views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that do nothing apart from just show the information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they're told to show and report back"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what events take place,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and those Views are controlled by Presenter classes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And the great thing about doing this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is these Presenter classes contain"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all the business logic for our application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and are completely unit testable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then we moved on to see how the Command pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can be particularly useful if you've got lots of buttons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""maybe on a toolbar or a menu in your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, we looked at the Event Aggregator pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is a great way to decouple the classes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that publish the events from those"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that subscribe to them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now not all of those techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will necessarily apply to every"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You may just want to select a couple of them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for yours."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But I would remind you to make sure"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you introduce these patterns as early as possible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Trying to retrofit them into an existing application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can be quite painful."",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you do make use of these patterns"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or refactor your application to use them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then you'll find that you'll end up with code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's easier to comprehend"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""easier to unit test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and easier to reuse,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whether within the same Windows Forms application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or even to take your business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and use it as the basis for a new application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""written with a different user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""framework, like WPF."",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now I do recognize we've covered a lot of ground"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in this module, and I certainly don't expect you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're completely new to the patterns we discussed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to have learned them in-depth"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the brief demonstrations that I've shown."",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The good news is that in the Pluralsight library"",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there are courses that cover all of these patterns"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and techniques in a much more systematic way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so make sure you check out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Patterns Library course at this URL,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which covers Model View Presenter,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Command pattern,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the Event Aggregator pattern."",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And also, I did point out several places"",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in which Inversion of Control containers"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""would help simplify our setup code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if you're interested in that topic,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""again there's a Pluralsight course"",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that explains what they are,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and demonstrates how to use several"",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the most popular ones."",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In our next module, we're going to move on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from the topic of maintainable code,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 178.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and look at how we can create our own"",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""custom controls in Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 182.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to allow ourselves to have complete control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.5796006
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""over their appearance and behavior."",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.5796006
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  ""title"": ""Creating Custom Controls"",
                  ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=0&mode=live"",
                  ""clips"": [
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Introduction"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=0&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Hi, my name's Mark Heath and in this module of our course"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on Windows Forms Best Practices on Pluralsight, we're going"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be talking about what's involved in creating your own"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""custom controls that you can use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""within your Windows Forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when you're creating a Windows Forms application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you actually have a lot of options at your disposal"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the controls that you are going to use."",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Obviously, there's the standard library of controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's part of the .NET Framework and for many applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""these would be perfectly sufficient for your needs."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also talked earlier in this course about the wealth of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""third party controls that are available, both open source"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and commercial, in fact, if you have a look at some"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the commercial Windows Forms Control libraries, there are"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""some very advanced controls available, like this Gantt chart"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for example, or this very nice-looking ColorPicker."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""These two examples are from a company called Telerik"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""who have a large library of Windows Forms controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There are several other companies offer"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""similar suites of controls and so may find that someone"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""has already done the hard work for you in creating controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that do what you need for your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But even with all of the third party controls that are"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""available, sometimes you find you do need to write your own."",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Because you have a particular appearance in mind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for exactly what you want your control to look like or"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you want to be in complete control of the way your control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""handles the mouse and response to keyboard events and"",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's what we are going to be looking at in this module."",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So the way we're going to approach this topic is to actually"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""build a Windows Forms custom control and we're going"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to build one for a demo application, which as you remember,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is an application for playing podcast episodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So what would be really nice is a display of the waveform"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the audio that we're listening to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'd like to be able to see what position playback"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is currently at and to be able to update the playback"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""position by clicking elsewhere on the waveform."",
                          ""displayTime"": 133.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this is a good example of the type of control that you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""won't typically find in third party control libraries."",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so we'll go through this step by step."",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll start off by talking about choosing an appropriate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""starting point field control, then we'll talk about how you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can render your control in Windows Forms and that's by using"",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""an API called GDI+ through the Graphics object so we'll be"",
                          ""displayTime"": 155.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""seeing what that is and how you can use it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then we'll update our control to support scrolling around"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the waveform and also, we'll talk about invalidation,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""making sure our control gets redrawn when it needs to be."",
                          ""displayTime"": 172.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then we'll update our control to support mouse interactions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we're going to allow you to click elsewhere in the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""control to reposition the current time cursor and then we'll"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""also look at something that possibly isn't really needed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for this particular control but is quite a common need when"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you're creating custom controls and that's drop-down panels"",
                          ""displayTime"": 194.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and so I'll show you how we can make a drop-down panel"",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""appear on this waveform when we right-click it to allow us"",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to enter notes about the podcast episode we're listening to."",
                          ""displayTime"": 205.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's get started."",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.0
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Choosing a Starting Point"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=1&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So when you're creating your own Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.5
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""custom control, what should you use as your starting point?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, there's actually several different options so"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'm going to run through them and then tell you which one"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're picking for our custom control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, you can inherit directly from"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""System.Windows.Forms.Control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This is if you like the base level control from which all"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all the other controls in the Windows Forms Control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""library inherit from."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It has no built-in appearance or behavior but it does have"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""quite a lot in there that will be useful to you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as access to the Paint, Mouse and Keyboard events."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, creating a custom control that inherits"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from Control really is very simple."",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Here you can see the entire code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for a custom control that just displays"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""an ellipse that fills the area of the control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Don't worry too much about this on Paint method,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to be talking about Graphics shortly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But here you can see what this control looks like"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when we put it on a Form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you do inherit from Control, you might be surprised"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to know that you can actually host child controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on your Control; however, you'd have to create them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and set all their properties in code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You wouldn't be able to do it with"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Windows Forms designer so we'll see an alternative way"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to host child controls in a moment."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But can also choose to inherit from any existing control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the Windows Forms library."",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Often, you'd do this when you want to override the behaviour"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the control but reuse it's existing appearance and"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's because quite often you'll find you can't fully"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""customize the appearance of existing Windows Forms controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Some of the controls in the Windows Forms library do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""however, offer an Owner Drawn mode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this allows you to override the appearance"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the control but reuse the behaviour."",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Examples of this are the ListView, the ComboBox"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the ToolTip so if for example, you wanted a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ComboBox but instead of text, you wanted different icons"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the ComboBox, then you could just use Owner Drawn mode."",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You wouldn't actually need to create your own custom"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""control to do that and the Windows Forms Class Library"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""actually contains some controls that are specifically"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""designed to be used as base classes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's ButtonBase which is inherited by the existing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Button, CheckBox and RadioButton controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Whenever I make a custom button class in Windows Forms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'll always inherit from ButtonBase rather than inheriting"",
                          ""displayTime"": 152.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from Control and there's also TextBoxBase which is inherited"",
                          ""displayTime"": 155.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by TextBox, MaskedTextBox and RichTextBox so if for example,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you wanted to make your own numeric textbox,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then inheriting from TextBoxBase would be a good choice."",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The final option is to inherit from UserControl."",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This is intended for when you're creating custom controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will contain child controls and in fact, we've already"",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""seen it in action in this course several times."",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, when we created all our Views"",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like the EpisodeView that you can see on the right here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It contains several existing Windows Forms Controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 192.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the benefit of the UserControl over just inheriting"",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from plain old Control is that we get designer support"",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so we can move these controls about in the designer"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and set their properties much more easily."",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It also inherits from ScrollableControl which means"",
                          ""displayTime"": 209.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that if it you want it to automatically scroll its contents"",
                          ""displayTime"": 212.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when it gets resized too small, you can take advantage"",
                          ""displayTime"": 216.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of that feature and the custom controls that you create"",
                          ""displayTime"": 219.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will automatically appear in the Toolbox allowing you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to drag them onto other forms and user controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 226.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and set their properties in the designer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And for the audio waveform control that we are going to make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in this module, we're actually going to choose UserControl"",
                          ""displayTime"": 235.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as the base class because I want to drop on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 238.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a horizontal scroll bar and so it's perfectly valid to use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 241.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the UserControl if you want to compose your custom control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 245.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""out of some existing controls and some parts of the display"",
                          ""displayTime"": 249.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you're going to draw yourself."",
                          ""displayTime"": 254.9584556
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's create our user control now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 256.9584556
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Creating a Custom Control"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=2&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's create a custom user control and we'll call it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Wave Form Viewer, we'll set its back color so we can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""see it a little bit more easily when we add it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to our EpisodeView and we want to add it to the EpisodeView"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but currently, it's not in our Toolbox because we haven't"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""built the project yet, so let's build the project and we can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""see the Wave Form Viewer appears in our Toolbox and we"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can add it to the EpisodeView."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And just like any other control we can set properties on it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like anchoring it to the bottom"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and now a custom control is created,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it just doesn't do anything yet."",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so now we can see our custom control in our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.7092001
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The next thing we want to do is to draw the waveform."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.7092001
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Drawing With GDI+"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=3&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as we said earlier, the way the Windows Forms allows you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to render your control is by making use of the GDI+ API."",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""GDI stands for Graphics Device Interface and you can access"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of its capabilities through the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""System.Drawing.Graphics class."",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It actually offers a very comprehensive drawing capabilities"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can draw shapes and lines including Bezier curves"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and polygons, you can make use of pens and brushes including"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""gradient and texture brushes or pattern-filled brushes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can draw text and existing images to the screen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can use any fonts installed on your system and"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the images that you paint can be painted in their"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""native size or stretched and scaled in any way"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and there are more advanced techniques that you can make use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of such as making use of anti-aliasing, transparency,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""rendering transforms and creating clipping regions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now the capabilities of this API mean that we'll only"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""scratch the surface of it in this course."",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll just be drawing some straight lines and rectangles"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but there's no reason why you can't make your"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""custom controls look exactly the way you want them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you've had a graphic designer mock-up some really"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""nice looking controls, then it will be possible with GDI"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to recreate those controls in Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So how do you render with GDI to your custom control?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, what you need to do is either handle the Paint event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or override the OnPaint method and when you do so,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll get access to the PaintEventArgs."",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This will give you the Graphics object with which you can do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all the drawing you need to do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It will also give you a Clip Rectangle."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This is a rectangle that needs to be repainted and"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this allows you to optimize your painting code and only"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""draw the things that need to be redrawn."",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""A word of caution is needed here, sometimes, it requires"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""quite a bit of thought to work out what ought to be redrawn"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're only trying to fill in a Clip Rectangle."",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So quite often in my Paint event handlers, I'll just"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""repaint the entire control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""A few other recommendations, you should perform all the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""painting you do inside the Paint event handler, if you don't"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you cold create graphics and paint outside the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Paint event handler then you will see what you paint"",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it won't persist on the screen and if another window"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is dragged over the top of yours and then off again,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the thing you painted will've disappeared."",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also it's often a very good idea to turn on double buffering"",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This reduces flicker when you're resizing your controls"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or scrolling around inside them."",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also for performance reasons, I would recommend"",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that if you're using any Brush, Pen, Image or Font resources"",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in the Paint event handler, then"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""don't create them every single time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 175.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Make them once and resuse them because your Paint event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""handler could get code multiple times a second."",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's actually put some of the GDI functions to use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.272289
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our custom control and draw a waveform."",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.272289
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Rendering the Waveform"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=4&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Ok, so the way we're going to draw audio waveforms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is by drawing vertical lines that represent how loud"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the audio is at each second so we need to have some"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""peak values and here I've added a method to the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Wave Form Viewer user control called Set Peaks"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is going to provide us with an array of peak values"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""zero means silence and one means maximum volume."",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And there'll be one peak for each second in the podcast"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this method is actually being called from"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our Presenter class when we load an episode"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if we haven't previously calculated the peaks"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for this episode, we're going to ask the podcast player to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""asynchronously create those peaks and then we'll tell"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the EpisodeView to set the peaks which just passes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""them on to the Wave Form Viewer user control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'm not going to show you how the peaks are calculated"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're interested in that then I explain how to do it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 56.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in detail in my Pluralsight course, Audio Programming with"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""NAudio but let's go back to my Wave Form Viewer and"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""let's draw the audio wave form when it becomes available."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The first thing I'm going to do is save the peaks to a field"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when they're set and then I'm going to code"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the invalidate function, this tells Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our control now needs to be redrawn."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The Paint event handler has to get code again."",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we didn't code this, our wave form wouldn't appear"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""until we resized the control or maybe dragged another"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""window over our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's implement the Paint event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'm going to override OnPaint and if we've got some peaks"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then first of all, we're just going to clear the background."",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'll do that by filling the rectangle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the Graphics subject."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I need a brush to fill the rectangle with so I'm going"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to create a brush called BackBrush and we need to specify"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the rectangle we're going to fill."",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In this case, I'm going to fill the entire Client Rectangle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our user control, if we were trying to optimize for only"",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""painting the Clip Rectangle, here we could"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just fill the Clip Rectangle."",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""As we said earlier, we want to make that brush a member"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our class so we don't need to keep recreating it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we're going to make use of the convenient"",
                          ""displayTime"": 145.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""back color property that's already on every"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms Control so if we haven't already created"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the BackBrush, we'll create a new Solid Color Brush"",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using the user's specified back color."",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now let's paint all the peaks so we need to loop through"",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our array of peaks, we need to calculate the height"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the line that we're going to draw."",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you remember peaks go from zero to one so if we have a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 170.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""peak of one, we'll use the maximum height available"",
                          ""displayTime"": 174.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our control but we want to center the line we draw"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the middle of our control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's calculate the white position of the top of the line"",
                          ""displayTime"": 183.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is height of the control minus the height of the line"",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""divided by two and now we can code DrawLine on our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Graphics object to draw the vertical line."",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're going to need a Pen to draw lines, Brushes fill shapes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 197.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Pens draw lines and outlines so we'll call this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Wave Form Pen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 204.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's starting x position is simply x because we're drawing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""one line per pixel, it's starting y position is top,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which we just calculated, it's ending x position is still x"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because it's a vertical line and it's ending y position"",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is the top of the line plus the height of the line."",
                          ""displayTime"": 222.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're nearly done. Let's just play that Wave Form Pen"",
                          ""displayTime"": 226.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using the ForeColor of the control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now there is one painting optimization that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 233.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we could do here and that's we're painting"",
                          ""displayTime"": 235.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""every vertical line in the entire waveform but"",
                          ""displayTime"": 238.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for a podcast that's an hour long that's 3,600 seconds."",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""That's going to be a lot wider than our custom control is."",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So actually we know that when the x position reaches the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 250.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""width of our control, then we don't need to draw any"",
                          ""displayTime"": 253.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""more peaks so let's put that optimization in even though"",
                          ""displayTime"": 256.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're not using the Clip Rectangle for optimization."",
                          ""displayTime"": 259.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we're ready to test our Start control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 264.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's run our application. We'll select a podcast."",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll have to wait a moment while it downloads"",
                          ""displayTime"": 273.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and creates the waveform but when it does it will appear"",
                          ""displayTime"": 275.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""instantly because we code invalidate and here we can see"",
                          ""displayTime"": 279.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the waveform for this episode."",
                          ""displayTime"": 283.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I resize our form wider, we're going to be able to see"",
                          ""displayTime"": 287.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""more peaks, you may have noticed some flicker there."",
                          ""displayTime"": 290.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""That's because I haven't got double buffer set up."",
                          ""displayTime"": 294.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's set up double buffering now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 297.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when I load this podcast, we don't have to wait"",
                          ""displayTime"": 304.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because I've now saved the peaks and when we"",
                          ""displayTime"": 307.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""resize, we get smooth resizing on our waveform"",
                          ""displayTime"": 309.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but what we can't do is scroll over to the right to see"",
                          ""displayTime"": 314.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the end of the waveform so that's what"",
                          ""displayTime"": 317.6163224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to add next."",
                          ""displayTime"": 320.6163224
                        }
                      ]
