                    {
                      ""title"": ""Repositioning With the Mouse"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=7&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now currently, our custom control does a good job"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of showing us the waveform and showing us where"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the current position is but what we'd like to do now"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to able to click on the waveform and for the position of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""playback to jump to that position so what we need to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is handle the Mouse events for our control and the good news"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is Windows Forms Controls make it very easy to get at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the various Mouse events that there are."",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can see here that we can handle MouseClick, MouseDown,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""MouseUp, there's MouseMove and various other Mouse events."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For our purposes, we need to handle the MouseClick event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which will fire when the mouse goes down and then"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""up again over our control so let's add an event handler."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We call it On MouseClick and the first thing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll typically do in the Mouse event handler is check"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which buttons clicked, in our case, we're only going"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to reposition when you click the left-mouse button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now we need to work out from the Mouse position"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where within the waveform do we need to reposition it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and for our custom control it's one pixel per second so the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""desired position that we want to move to in seconds is the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""x coordinate of the Mouse event args and we also need to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""take into account the value of the horizontal scroll bar."",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you've scrolled across a bit, then x is not doesn't"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""mean the start of the file so we'll add on the value"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the horizontal scroll bar, now one thing to bear in"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""mind with these coordinates on Mouse event args,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they're in terms of the control, not the screen so if you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""click in the top left-hand corner of your control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll get coordinates of x is zero and y is zero."",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now we can simply set the Position in Seconds property"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we just created."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's run that and see what happens."",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now if I click somewhere on the waveform, we'll see that our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""position bar jumps to the new position and shows"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where we clicked and if we scroll across somewhere into"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the middle of the waveform and we click right over"",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""at the left, we'll see we've repositioned"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to 14 minutes in and not to a few seconds."",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now it may look at this point like we're done with this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""feature but actually all we're doing is updating this marker"",
                          ""displayTime"": 140.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on our control, we've not actually told the rest of the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""application that anything's changed."",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So to enable that, we need to have an event that we can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""raise that users of our control can subscribe to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to know when the user has clicked in order to reposition."",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll call our event Position Changed and we'll make a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 161.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Helper method that raises that event when we need to and"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we need to code that method when the user repositions."",
                          ""displayTime"": 169.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you're wondering why I didn't put this code into the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Position in Seconds setter that's to avoid this event firing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""every time the position is updated from outside the control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for example, during playback when we update it every second."",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll need to make a couple of changes in our EpisodeView"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the View interface needs to be able to report"",
                          ""displayTime"": 193.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the position has been changed as well and we can do that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""simply by passing on the event from our custom control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, this means that in the Presenter, we can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""subscribe to this event and tell the podcast player"",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we want to update the current position of playback."",
                          ""displayTime"": 210.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So now if we test our application and we start playing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""an episode, you'll see that now if we click on the waveform"",
                          ""displayTime"": 219.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to reposition, we'll actually reposition where we're playing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 222.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the playback will continue from our new position."",
                          ""displayTime"": 226.2768115
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""(mouse clicks)"",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.2768115
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Drag and Scroll Repositioning"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=8&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now clicking to reposition is quite nice but what if we'd"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like to be able to drag that playback cursor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to a new position as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""How can we do that?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well the first thing we need to do is detect when the mouse"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""goes over that playback cursor and we can do that by"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""handling the MouseMove event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We get to MouseMove event whenever the mouse"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""cursor moves over our control and we want to see if the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""mouse is currently over that Now position vertical bar."",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we can actually use the same calculation we used before."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we take the x position of the mouse and add on the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""scroll bar value, then that's the Position in Seconds into"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the file that the user's mouse is over and so we'll test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to see not just if the mouse is exactly over that line"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""cause that might be a bit fiddly, will allow it to be up to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""five pixels either side of the line so if the mouse is close"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""enough to the line, we're going to change our cursor."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And Windows Forms has some built-in cursors, we're"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""going to use the Size West/East cursor, which shows an"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""arrow that points both left and right indicating you can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""drag horizontally and, of course, if your mouse isn't over"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Play position, then we need to put"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the cursor back to its default value."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we run this, you'll see that when my mouse goes right to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the left-hand side of the control, the cursor changes to the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""left-right arrow but ,of course, dragging doesn't actually"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""happen yet so now we need to support actually dragging it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""To do that, we'll handle the MouseDown event and when"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the mouse goes down on our control, we're going to check"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""two things: first, was it the left-mouse button and second,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is the cursor currently back drag cursor?"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We could, of course, use another flag that we set in on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""MouseMove but this is convenient for now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If it is, we'll set a flag to say that now,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're currently dragging the cursor."",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now in the MouseMove event, if we're not dragging, we'll"",
                          ""displayTime"": 133.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just do what we did before but if we are currently dragging,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we'll set the Position in Seconds to the Hover position"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Note, that we're not going to raise our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Position changed event at this point, we don't want to be"",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""firing loads of these as you move the mouse around."",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're going to fire it when you finish dragging by releasing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the left-mouse button so we need to handle the MouseUp"",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""event as well and if the Mouse button is the left button"",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we're currently dragging then we'll stop dragging."",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll put the cursor back to normal and we'll raise"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our event, now, let's try this to see what it looks like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you can see now as I click and drag, that the Now cursor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 186.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""moves along and keeps us updated with what the position"",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'm dragging over is, however, if we were playing,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 194.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we wouldn't actually update the position in the file"",
                          ""displayTime"": 199.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we were playing until we release the mouse button."",
                          ""displayTime"": 201.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now this is a fairly basic implementation of scroll"",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""reposition, there's a few extra nice things we could do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 209.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as if you drag off the right-hand side, we could"",
                          ""displayTime"": 213.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""automatically scroll away from to bring the area"",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you're trying to scroll into, into view and we should"",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""also probably try to protect ourselves from trying"",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to reposition before the begining of the code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 225.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now you may wonder how that's possible"",
                          ""displayTime"": 229.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because if I put a conditional breakpoint in MouseMove"",
                          ""displayTime"": 232.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which fires when the Mouse event args x position is"",
                          ""displayTime"": 236.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""less than zero and then we launch our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 238.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I wiggle my mouse over the start"",
                          ""displayTime"": 245.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the control the breakpoint isn't hit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 247.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'm not getting MouseMove events when the mouse is outside"",
                          ""displayTime"": 250.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the control, however, if I click to start dragging and"",
                          ""displayTime"": 253.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""now I drag past the left-hand side of the control, I'm"",
                          ""displayTime"": 258.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""capturing the mouse and so my breakpoint is going to be hit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 261.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I'm now getting MouseMove events that are actually"",
                          ""displayTime"": 266.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""outside the bounds of my control so if you do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 268.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""try to implement this in your own controls, be aware"",
                          ""displayTime"": 271.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the fact that when the Mouse button is pressed,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 274.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you can get MouseMove events outside"",
                          ""displayTime"": 277.6391671
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the bounds of your control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 279.6391671
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Creating Drop-Down Forms"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=9&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Ok, so we're going to add just one last feature"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to our custom control and that's when we right-click it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we want a little drop-down window to appear, a bit like"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a drop-down that you'd see on a ComboBox and it will allow"",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""us to type in a note so that we can make notes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""about the episode at the time that we right-clicked."",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What we need to do first of all is"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""create a Form for our drop-down"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I'll call it Note Form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It needs a couple of special properties setting on it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, the Start position needs to be manual"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because we are going to position this exactly"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the Form Border style needs to be set to none."",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll also give it a different background color"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""so we can see it more easily."",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now we're going to add a label which says Enter Note"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and a textbox which we'll call Text Box Note"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for them to enter the note in and this drop-down form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""doesn't need to be very big."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so now in our control, we need to make that Form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""appear if we right-clicked inside our control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so I've written some code to handle this when the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""right button is clicked, we work out the desired position in"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""seconds and we actually set the position then we create our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""new Note Form and to work out where to put it we're going to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""use PointToScreen on the coordinates of the mouse-click"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""PointToScreen takes coordinates that are in terms of a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""control and turns them into absolute screen coordinates so"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this allows us to set exactly where the Form should appear."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then we show the Form and when the Form is closed,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 110.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to examine what was entered in the textbox"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and if anything was entered in the textbox, then we're"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""going to fire a new event called the Note created event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the Note created event will say what note you typed in"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and what time the position cursor was at."",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also to make this Form behave like a drop-down form"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on a ComboBox, we need to handle the deactivate event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This happens when the user clicks outside of the Form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It loses focuses. We want to close the Form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Doesn't need to stay open if it loses focus and we also need"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a way of getting at the text that the user entered"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and finally in our Presenter, we're going to need to handle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Note created event and when we get a Note created event"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're simply going to format the time and the message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that was entered and add it to the Note's textbox"",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we already have in the current EpisodeView."",
                          ""displayTime"": 166.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's have a look at what this now looks like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now when I right-click somewhere on the waveform,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""(mouse clicks)"",
                          ""displayTime"": 179.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we see this little textbox appear."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I can type into it and then when I click away somewhere"",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""(mouse clicks)"",
                          ""displayTime"": 189.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll see my note appears here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 191.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I can scroll across to the right and put another note"",
                          ""displayTime"": 194.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""somewhere else in the waveform."",
                          ""displayTime"": 198.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""(Mouse and keyboard clicks)"",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so there you can see a simple way to create"",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.7272449
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""drop-down panels for your custom controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 208.7272449
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Summary"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m6&clip=10&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In this module, we've learned about how you can create"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""custom controls for your Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by creating our own Wave Form Viewer Control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We talked first of all about choosing the most appropriate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""starting point for your custom control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can actually inherit right from the base control class"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or as we did in this demo from UserControl but those"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""aren't the only choices, there are base classes designed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be inherited from or you can inherit from any existing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms Control and we also mentioned the fact that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there were some controls that support owner drawing so you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""may not always need to create a custom control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We then saw in this module several examples of how you can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""use the power of the GDI+ API to control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the appearance of your control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now as you can see from the screenshot, my own GDI skills"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""aren't particularly impressive but that's not because of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""any limitations in the platform, it really does support"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""pretty much everything that you would"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""need from a drawing API."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""When you are painting your own control, remember to perform"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all painting in the Paint event and make use of double"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""buffering to ensure your control resizes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and scrolls smoothly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you do want to optimize, you can make use of the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Clip Rectangle and only paint what you know is visible"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""at the time like we did, not painting all of the peaks"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but only the ones that fitted into our view and we also saw"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the importance of remembering to code invalidate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""whenever any properties that might change what the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""appearance of your control is are changed and we saw"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as well how you could use the Graphics MeasureString"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""method in order to calculate the size that a string will be"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when you render it, which allowed us to get this rectangle"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be the right width and we also saw that you don't"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""necessarily have to render the entire control yourself."",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We combined some GDI painting with a scroll bar and so"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""got some behaviour for free."",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also saw how handling Mouse events allows the user to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""interact in your control and make their"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""own changes and edits."",
                          ""displayTime"": 133.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We saw examples of handling MouseClick, MouseDown"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and MouseUp and you do need to remember to check"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which mouse button has been clicked in those events."",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also saw the MouseMove event in action and how we"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can set the mouse cursor in order to give hints of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what the user can do within our control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we also saw, that you should raise some events"",
                          ""displayTime"": 156.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to report when the user has done something that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 159.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the user of your control might be interested in being"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""notified of and in our control, that was when"",
                          ""displayTime"": 164.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they repositioned or added a note."",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, we saw the use of drop-down panels."",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The drop-down panel is actually a Form in its own right."",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It has a border style of none and it has a start position"",
                          ""displayTime"": 180.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of manual and we calculate that position using"",
                          ""displayTime"": 184.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""PointToScreen which turns coordinates in terms of our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 187.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""user control into absolute screen coordinates and to make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 191.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this drop-down form go away, we simply close it when"",
                          ""displayTime"": 196.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we get the Deactivate event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 200.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So I hope you found this module helpful and interesting,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 203.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of course, in the short time we had, we couldn't show"",
                          ""displayTime"": 206.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""everything about creating a custom control but hopefully,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 208.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've shown you a good variety of the types of thing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 211.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can do in your own custom control and inspired you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to maybe create some of your own."",
                          ""displayTime"": 218.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In our next module, we're going to be looking at other ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 221.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we can add new capabilities to our Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 223.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""applications by interoperating with other technologies"",
                          ""displayTime"": 226.5463783
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as web browsers and hosting WPF controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 231.5463783
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  ""title"": ""Interoperability"",
                  ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=0&mode=live"",
                  ""clips"": [
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Introduction"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=0&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Hi, my name's Mark Heath, and in this module"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our Windows Forms Best Practices course on Pluralsight,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to be looking at some ways you can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""extend the capabilities of your Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""through interoperating with other technologies."",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, in our last module, we looked at how you can"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""create your own custom Windows Forms control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the ones provided as standard,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or the ones available from third parties,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""don't do quite what you need."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But even if you create your own custom controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there'll still be some times where you come up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""against the limitations of Windows Forms itself."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so this module is about"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how we can overcome those limitations,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and extend our Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to do things that Windows Forms itself can't do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""By interoperating with other technologies."",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'm going to show three ways that you can do this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, we'll talk about accessing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the full capabilities of the Windows operating system,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by making calls into Windows APIs,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""through a technology called Platform Invoke."",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll also see how you can intercept and examine"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Windows messages that your application is being sent."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then we'll look at a way that you can host web content"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""within your application, by making use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the web browser control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This allows you to display static HTML,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as well as loading web pages from the internet."",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It provides a way that you can examine,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and even manipulate, the DOM,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's the Document Object Model, using .NET code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll be seeing these techniques in action,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, we'll see how you can host WPF controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""within a Windows Forms application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by making use of the ElementHost control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll see how this could be a way,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for those of you who would like to migrate away"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from Windows Forms to WPF, to incrementally migrate,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""converting part of your user interface to WPF,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""while the rest of it remains as Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.0
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Invoking Windows APIs"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=1&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, first of all, although the Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""controls and classes expose some of the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""most commonly used Windows features,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""they certainly don't expose everything"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you might want to use."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""However, you are not limited"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to what Windows Forms offers you."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can call any Windows API"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from a Windows Forms application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and to do so, you need to make use"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of what's called Platform Invoke, or P/Invoke."",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This involves creating method signatures"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the methods you want to call,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and also quite often creating managed versions"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the structures that need to be passed to those methods."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The good news is that very often"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you don't need to do this yourself,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you can go to websites like pinvoke.net,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and find the interrupt signatures"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the methods you want to call."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also, in Windows applications, your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is being sent messages from the Windows operating system."",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms intercepts some of those messages for you,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like the mouse and keyboard events,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and presents them to you in an easy to use way."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you're not limited just to the ones"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the Windows Forms API makes available to you."",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You can examine any Windows message"",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's sent to your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by overriding the WindProc function."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So I would recommend being nosy,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and having a look and seeing what messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your application is being sent."",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you write a simple function like this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that overrides WindProc and simply"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""writes out a debug message showing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the message that's been received,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll find all kinds of messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are being sent to your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 97.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, there's a message called WM_DEVICECHANGE,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you'll receive every time someone plugs in"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or unplugs a USB key from the computer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""To illustrate calling WIndows APIs"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and examining Windows messages,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll see how we can add"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""touch capabilities to our application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""even though Windows Forms doesn't include"",
                          ""displayTime"": 121.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""any support for touchscreens,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you can still respond to touch events"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from within your Windows Forms application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What you have to do is register"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you're interested in touch messages,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 133.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because Windows doesn't send them to you by default."",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you do that by calling the RegisterTouchWindow,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows API, and this API is available"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in Windows 7 and above, so you can't"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""make use of it on Vista or XP."",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And then, having registered for touch messages,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you would override WndProc,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you'd look out for the WM_TOUCH messages."",
                          ""displayTime"": 155.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""When you receive one, you still need to make sense"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the parameters that have been sent to you,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 162.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you do that by calling another Windows API,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 165.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""called GetTouchInputInfo."",
                          ""displayTime"": 168.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, in the Windows 7 SDK,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 171.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's actually a really nice little demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that shows you exactly how to do what I've just described"",
                          ""displayTime"": 176.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in a Windows Forms application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 179.5564667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's run that up, and see it in action."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.5564667
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Touch Support Demo"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=2&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here I've loaded up our touch demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I'm running it on a touchscreen monitor."",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if I put my fingers on the screen and drag them down,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you'll see that in this application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it simply draws a line showing me"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where my fingers have touched."",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's have a look at the code that was required to do this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, first of all, you can see here"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that when we get the form load event,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we call RegisterTouchWindow."",
                          ""displayTime"": 32.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If I look at the definition of this,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll see that it's a platform invoke method signature,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's calling into a Windows API, that's in the User 32 DLL"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this tells Windows that we want"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to receive those WM touch events."",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And having called that,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this means that now in the WindProc method,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is being overridden here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we simply have a look at the message,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and see if it's a WM touch message."",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again, WM touch is simply a constant that we can find"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in one of the Windows SDK header files."",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Or in online documentation."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we have got a touch message,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we need to decode it,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is done in the decode touch method."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you can see here that we're calling"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into another Windows API, called GetTouchInputInfo,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is also in the User 32 DLL."",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This provides us with some touch input structures,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which will give us much more detailed information"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""about what kind of touch gesture took place."",
                          ""displayTime"": 100.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, the point of showing you this isn't to teach you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""how to implement touch support in your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or to teach you how to do platform invoke."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's simply to show you what's possible"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you're willing to make some calls into Windows APIs."",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It allows you to access more advanced features of Windows,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that aren't supported by the Windows Forms class library."",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so using these APIs, you'd be able to make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a Windows Forms application that was right at home"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.0305667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on a touchscreen Windows tablet, like the new Surface 3 Pro."",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.0305667
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Hosting Web Content"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=3&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The next technique I want to discuss"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for extending the capabilities"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of your Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is embedding web content inside your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by making use of the web browser control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now this is actually a Windows Forms control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and what it gives you is Internet Explorer,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""embedded within your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It uses whatever version of Internet Explorer"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is installed on your machine,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""although it has one particularly frustrating property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's that it always defaults to IE7 compatibility,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and there isn't an easy programmatic way to change this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What you need to do if you want it render"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your pages in IE9, 10 or 11 mode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is actually to set a registry key,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or, if you're in control of the HTML that's being rendered,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's a meta tag that you can put at the top of your page,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to say that you want standards compliant rendering."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's just have a look at a few of the more interesting"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""properties on the web browser control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then we'll see how it could be a useful addition"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 65.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, there's the navigate method."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This allows you to specify the URL"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of a webpage that you want to load."",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's also the DocumentText property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which will get the HTML if you've just loaded a page,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but you can also use it to set a fragment of HTML"",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you want the control to render."",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then there's the document property,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and this is very powerful, because it allows you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to access the DOM as a HtmlDocument class."",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And this allows you to explore the DOM,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and also to make changes and manipulate it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Another very interesting capability is that you can provide"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what's called an ObjectForScripting."",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This is a .NET object that you want"",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to allow the JavaScript on the page you've loaded,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to be able to examine and call methods on."",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So this control really does allow two-way communication,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from your Windows Forms app to the webpage,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and from the webpage back to your Windows Forms app."",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And there are some other useful properties,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""like you can disallow navigation, for example,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you want to make sure that only specific webpages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you're in control of are ever displayed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 134.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""within your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 137.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And another useful one is to suppress script errors,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because particularly if you're in IE7 compatibility mode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 143.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you're very likely to get some popup javascript errors"",
                          ""displayTime"": 147.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""appearing when you load a webpage."",
                          ""displayTime"": 150.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's put the web browser control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 153.9894779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to use in our demo application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 154.9894779
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""WebBrowser Demo"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=4&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, first of all, when we select a podcast tree node"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in our demo application, we have this rather bland view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the right, which we called the podcast view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's just got the title of the podcast,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and the number of episodes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""What would be really cool would be really cool"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is if we could show the homepage for that podcast"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""underneath, on the right."",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's do that with the web browser control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll drag the web browser control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""onto our podcast view user control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We'll anchor it to all fours sides."",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we'll suppress script errors,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because I haven't set that registry key"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that will make this render with the latest version of IE."",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, in the code for our podcast view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 47.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll add a new method to our podcast view interface,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to allow us to set the podcast URL."",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And when that method is called,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll use the navigate method of the web browser control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to navigate to that URL."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And finally, when a podcast is selected,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we need to call that set podcast URL method."",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's run this, and see what that looks like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, when we select a podcast tree node,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to see the homepage"",
                          ""displayTime"": 82.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for our podcast load up on the right."",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And if we switch to a different podcast,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it will take a moment,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it will load the homepage up for that as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now there is one other place in this application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""where the web browser control might be useful."",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we look at one of the podcast episodes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll see that often the description includes some HTML,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 102.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but because we're putting it in a label,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it doesn't really render nicely."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It doesn't show links, or bold, or italic text."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So we could put the description as a HTML fragment"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""into a web browser in the episode view, as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.4002668
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's do that, quickly."",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.4002668
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Rendering HTML Fragments"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=5&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here, in the episode view, I've deleted the label"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that was previously showing the episode description,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and replaced it with another web browser control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And again, I've set it to suppress script errors."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The only code change I needed to make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""was in the episode view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when the description was set by our presenter,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""now instead of setting the label text,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're setting the document text property of the web browser."",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's run this and see what it looks like."",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If we now load up an episode again,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll see that here our web browser control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is now rendering that HTML fragment,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""including the links."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Although, in this example, we might want"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to turn off navigating for this web browser,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""because it's really too small to show a whole webpage in."",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we might also want to put in some CSS dialing,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to make it use a nicer looking font."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's just look now at one more capability"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the web browser control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's accessing and manipulating the DOM,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.1518335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""using the document property of the web browser control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.1518335
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Accessing the DOM"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=6&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so here we are back in the podcast view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I've added an event handler"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the web browser's document completed event."",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This event is fired whenever a webpage"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""completes loading in the web browser control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So when a webpage completes loading,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""what we're going to do is we're going to go through"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the document which gives us access to the DOM,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and look at all of the HTML elements."",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'm using links cast method here,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to give us a strongly type collection."",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I'm just looking at all of the tags with the name of A,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's all of the links within the document."",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And whenever I find a link, I'm going to change"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the inner text of that tag to Pluralsight,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and set the URL to the main Pluralsight homepage."",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So no matter what webpage we load up,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all the links on it are now"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""going to point us back to Pluralsight."",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's have a look, and see this in action."",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's select the Herding Code podcast."",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you'll see on the right, the page loads up normally,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but shortly afterwards, all of the links"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""change their text to Pluralsight,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and also their destinations to Pluralsight."",
                          ""displayTime"": 71.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So if we click on one of these links,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 74.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we'll navigate to the Pluralsight homepage."",
                          ""displayTime"": 76.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And unfortunately, as you can see,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the Pluralsight homepage doesn't support IE7."",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So this would be an example of when"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we would probably want to set that registry key,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to ensure that the web browser control we're using"",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""isn't running in an old compatability mode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but is running with the latest web standards"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are supported by Internet Explorer."",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Obviously, this is a ridiculous example,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but hopefully it show you the capabilities that you have"",
                          ""displayTime"": 105.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to examine and manipulate the DOM from within your code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 108.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's move on now and see our final technique"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for extending Windows Forms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.8464335
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and that's by embedding WPF content within our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 118.8464335
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Hosting WPF Content"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=7&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now, in our demo application, this episode view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you can see on the right"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is the most complicated view that we have."",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's got a custom waveform control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's now also got a web browser control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and several other controls as well."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We may be feeling that we're starting to reach"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the limitations of what we can do in Windows Forms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and maybe we're thinking this would be easier"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to implement if we would be using WPF."",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's what the element host control allows us to do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So let's have a look at how we would do that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here, I've created a WPF version of this episode view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's got the same information,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 44.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it's actually also using WPF's web browser control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to show the description."",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It's using a slider for the rating,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I've even made a custom WPF control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that show the waveform and allows you to update the position"",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just like we did in Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So how can we swap out the Windows Forms episode view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with this WPF version of the same view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Well, what we need to do is create another"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms user control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that is going to host our WPF episode view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So here I've created a new, blank Windows Forms user control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and I've called it WPF Episode View Host."",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And what we're going to do is drag on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the WPF element host control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which is available here, in the toolbox."",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're going to dock it to fill its entire parent container."",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now we can specify which WPF control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to put inside."",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""I've got two WPF controls in this project,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there's the waveform control and the episode view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's the episode view that I want here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 120.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Now what we need to do is to implement"",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the I episode view interface, so that we can swap it out"",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the existing implementation of that view interface."",
                          ""displayTime"": 131.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So in the code behind for this control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 136.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""let's say that we implement I episode view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 139.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and as we learned in our module on maintainable code,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all the code inside our view implementation"",
                          ""displayTime"": 148.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""should really be quite trivial and straightforward."",
                          ""displayTime"": 151.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so here you can see I've implemented"",
                          ""displayTime"": 155.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the I view interface, simply by passing on"",
                          ""displayTime"": 157.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the property setters and getters"",
                          ""displayTime"": 160.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the appropriate controls in the WPF user control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 163.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which here is just called WPF episode view one."",
                          ""displayTime"": 167.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The same's also true of the events"",
                          ""displayTime"": 173.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that are raised by the waveform control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 175.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For when the position has been changed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 177.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""or when a note's been created."",
                          ""displayTime"": 179.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We're just passing them on."",
                          ""displayTime"": 181.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as you can see, there's nothing complicated in here."",
                          ""displayTime"": 182.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've just swapped out a Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 186.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""implementation of the view interface,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 188.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for a WPF implementation of the same view interface."",
                          ""displayTime"": 190.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The only thing that remains to do,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 195.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is to actually switch which concrete class we're using."",
                          ""displayTime"": 197.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's done in the main form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 202.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Instead of the old episode view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 205.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're now going to use WPF episode view host."",
                          ""displayTime"": 207.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And that's all there is to it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 214.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's run this and check that it works."",
                          ""displayTime"": 215.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And now when we select an episode,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 220.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can see our new WPF implementation of the episode view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 224.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the right hand panel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 228.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And as before, we can drag and update the playback position,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 230.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and we can add our own notes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 234.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And in fact, the note functionality"",
                          ""displayTime"": 240.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is one example of where the WPF control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 242.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""doesn't work quite right,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 246.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when it's hosted inside an element host."",
                          ""displayTime"": 248.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We have some troubles getting keyboard focus"",
                          ""displayTime"": 251.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""onto the textbox in the dropdown."",
                          ""displayTime"": 253.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And so that's something you do need to be aware of,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 256.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""when you're hosting your WPF controls inside an element host"",
                          ""displayTime"": 259.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for the most part it does work well,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 263.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but you might find the odd little quirk"",
                          ""displayTime"": 265.2729224
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that you need to work around."",
                          ""displayTime"": 267.2729224
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Incremental Migration"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=8&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""One of the interesting possibilities that's opened up"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by the technologies that we've been looking at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in this module, is that you could start"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to migrate your application incrementally,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to make use of a new technology,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""such as HTML5 or WPF."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Often, with a line of business application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that's been around for many years,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 22.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""it will have hundreds of different screens and capabilities,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it's not possible to convert the whole thing in one go."",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But you could start to convert piece by piece."",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""For example, you could begin to make"",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a HTML5 website that has some of the functionality"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of your Windows Forms application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and then update your Windows Forms application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to present those parts of the user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""simply using the web browser control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Of course, it's not going to be completely seamless,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""but it is a way that you can start to migrate"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from a purely Windows Forms based application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 58.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""over to a single page web app,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""without having to do it all in one go."",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you don't like the web browser control"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and you'd rather not be using IE,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 68.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""there are actually other options,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""including embedding the Chrome browser."",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And I've provided a link here to one of a number of projects"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that allow you to do just this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 78.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Alternatively, you may decide"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that it's WPF that you want to go to,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and to start writing your new"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""user interface components with Zamel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Again, you don't have to do it all in one hit."",
                          ""displayTime"": 91.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""By making use of the element host control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 93.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we just looked at, you can select"",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""parts of your application to be reimplemented in WPF."",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we also saw, in that last demo,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just what a great benefit"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""having used the Model View Presenter pattern is."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Because we were able to reuse"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of our model and presenter classes,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""without any changes at all."",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The only thing that we needed to do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 117.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""was simply reimplement the view using WPF,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""instead of with Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In fact, in our demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 126.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we've already ported the most complicated view."",
                          ""displayTime"": 127.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It wouldn't take too long to completely"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.8316558
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""turn this app now into a WPF application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.8316558
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Summary"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m7&clip=9&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So as we said at the beginning,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""this module has been all about"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""pushing past the limitations of Windows Forms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 5.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and using the power of other technologies,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in order to enhance the capabilities"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our Windows Forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We saw how, in Windows Forms,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you can easily call any Windows API that you want to,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by making use of Platform Invoke."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And you can also view all the Windows messages"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that your application receives,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 27.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by overriding the WindProc function."",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then we looked at how you can embed"",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""web pages in your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by making use of the web browser control,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 37.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which does have a few quirks,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""particularly the fact that it uses IE7 rendering by default."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But there are ways that you can address that."",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""One of its very cool features is that it allows you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to programmatically interact with the DOM,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and it also allows you to simply render HTML fragments."",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we also saw how you can embed WPF controls,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to make use of some of the richer rendering capabilities"",
                          ""displayTime"": 63.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of the WPF platform."",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You do this by embedding them within an ElementHost control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we saw how this might be a way,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 73.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you wanted to migrate away"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from Windows Forms to a newer technology,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to migrate incrementally,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""converting parts of your application a bit at a time."",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""And we also saw how,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""if you were using the model view presenter pattern,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then this is going to make life much easier."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You'll only need to reimplement the views,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and all of your business logic"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""is just going to keep working."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've almost reached the end of our course, now."",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In the final module, we're going to be reviewing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.6497003
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of the things that we've looked at in this course."",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.6497003
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  ""title"": ""Conclusion"",
                  ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m8&clip=0&mode=live"",
                  ""clips"": [
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Module Introduction"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m8&clip=0&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Hi."",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""My name's Mark Heath."",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In this final, brief module of our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms Best Practices course,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we're going to summarizing the main things"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that we've learned throughout this course."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We can break up the best practices recommendations"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and techniques that we've been looking at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""throughout this course into three broad categories."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, we looked at various ways in which"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can enhance the user experience,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""making sure that our Windows Forms applications"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""are meeting the needs of all our users."",
                          ""displayTime"": 33.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also looked at several different ways that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we can improve the way that we write our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 40.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms code in order to make it"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""more maintainable, extensible and testable."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, we saw a number of options that are"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""available to you for when what Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""offers out of the box isn't enough to meet your needs."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, we saw several ways that you can extend"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the capabilities of your Windows Forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Let's just review some of the key best practices"",
                          ""displayTime"": 67.0
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""from each of these three areas."",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.0
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""User Experience"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m8&clip=1&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, first of all, we've seen many different ways"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in which we can improve the user experience, and this"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""really is about considering the needs of all the users"",
                          ""displayTime"": 8.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of our application and ensuring that their use of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your application is as smooth and successful"",
                          ""displayTime"": 14.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""as possible."",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, we talked about making your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 18.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""resizable, and we did that in our demo application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by making use, not just of the dock and anchor"",
                          ""displayTime"": 24.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""properties on controls, but also using some of the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""container controls, like SplitContainer,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 29.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""TableLayout Panel and FlowLayout Panel."",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also talked about the importance of choosing"",
                          ""displayTime"": 35.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""an appropriate layout for your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""avoiding clutter."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Don't put every single control, option and feature"",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all on one screen."",
                          ""displayTime"": 45.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""In our demo application, we chose an"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Explorer style layout, where you have tree view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""on the left-hand side and then a details view,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 52.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""dependent on what tree node is selected on the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""right-hand side."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""You should also consider making your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 59.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""keyboard navigable, and we saw how you can do"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that with hot keys and making use of mnemonics."",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Something that's quite often overlooked is making"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your application accessible to those who are"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""blind or partially sighted."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We saw how we could enhance our demo application by"",
                          ""displayTime"": 77.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""supporting large fonts and high-contrast color schemes."",
                          ""displayTime"": 80.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Then, there's some of the basic principles of usability,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 85.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""just helping the user to know what to do by making"",
                          ""displayTime"": 88.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""use of tool tips or finding other ways to guide"",
                          ""displayTime"": 90.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the user of your application into making the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 94.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""correct choices."",
                          ""displayTime"": 96.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""When something does go wrong in your application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 99.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""help the user to know what the problem is, with"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""well-worded error messages, or as we saw in our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 104.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""demo, the use of the ErrorProvider."",
                          ""displayTime"": 107.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, for those users of your application from"",
                          ""displayTime"": 111.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""different cultures or who speak different languages,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 114.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then we saw how we can localize our Windows Forms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 116.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""application, and we saw how that goes beyond just"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""simply translating the strings in the forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 123.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""It also involves potentially changing the layout of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 125.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Also, translating strings that come from other"",
                          ""displayTime"": 129.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""parts of our application and remembering that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""localization also includes things like the way that"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""dates and times are formatted."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, if you take the time to address each of these"",
                          ""displayTime"": 141.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""areas in your Windows Forms application,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 144.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then it will go a long way towards making your"",
                          ""displayTime"": 146.7425889
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""users really enjoy using your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 149.7425889
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Coding Practices"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m8&clip=2&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""The second main area that we looked at was"",
                          ""displayTime"": 0.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""various coding practices, and this really is about"",
                          ""displayTime"": 3.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""ensuring that future developers are able to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""continue maintaining and extending our"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""application and ensuring we can effectively test"",
                          ""displayTime"": 12.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 15.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, this involves making sure that you have"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a good strategy for handling exceptions, both"",
                          ""displayTime"": 19.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""anticipated exceptions, ways in which you know"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""particular functions might go wrong in your"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""application, and also unanticipated exceptions,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""which can be dealt with in a global exception handler."",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also saw how you can put long-running tasks"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""onto background threads and that there are many"",
                          ""displayTime"": 39.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""different ways you can do this."",
                          ""displayTime"": 42.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But, if you are able to use the async and await"",
                          ""displayTime"": 43.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""keywords, then they really can simplify your"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""threading code."",
                          ""displayTime"": 49.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Some of the practices we looked at were"",
                          ""displayTime"": 51.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""quite simple, and yet often forgotten, like"",
                          ""displayTime"": 53.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""giving all of your controls meaningful names."",
                          ""displayTime"": 55.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also saw how you can segregate your user"",
                          ""displayTime"": 60.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""interface into smaller user controls, rather than putting"",
                          ""displayTime"": 62.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""all of your controls onto one monolithic main form."",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""This gives a lot of advantages, not just in terms"",
                          ""displayTime"": 70.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of code maintainability, but also allowing you to"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""resize more easily and even make radical changes"",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to the way your application is laid out."",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also saw with our demo application how we"",
                          ""displayTime"": 83.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can get the business logic out of the code behind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 86.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""in order that it can be tested with automated tests,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""rather than only being able to be tested with a"",
                          ""displayTime"": 92.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""manual run of the application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 95.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We saw a number of patterns that may be really"",
                          ""displayTime"": 98.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""useful to help you do that, particularly the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 101.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Model View Presenter pattern, which is a great"",
                          ""displayTime"": 103.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""way of getting all of the business logic out of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 106.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""your views."",
                          ""displayTime"": 109.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also saw how the Command pattern"",
                          ""displayTime"": 112.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""can be helpful, when you've got lots of buttons,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 113.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""say on a tool bar, and an Event Aggregator"",
                          ""displayTime"": 115.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""may also be a good fit for your application if"",
                          ""displayTime"": 119.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""you want to be able to more easily decouple"",
                          ""displayTime"": 122.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""publishers and subscribers to events."",
                          ""displayTime"": 124.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, if you take these recommendations and apply"",
                          ""displayTime"": 128.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""them to your Windows Forms applications,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 130.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""then you'll find that future development isn't"",
                          ""displayTime"": 132.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""nearly as painful as it can quite often be with large"",
                          ""displayTime"": 135.9583667
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""legacy Windows forms applications."",
                          ""displayTime"": 138.9583667
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""Extensibility"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m8&clip=3&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Finally, we saw in this course that there are"",
                          ""displayTime"": 2.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""several options available to you when you find"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that the controls that are provided as standard with"",
                          ""displayTime"": 6.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms don't do everything that you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 9.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""need them to do."",
                          ""displayTime"": 11.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""First of all, there's a wide variety of third-party"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""controls, both open source and commercial,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 16.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""that may be a perfect fit for your application."",
                          ""displayTime"": 20.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""But, if you can't find the exact control you need,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""we also saw how you can create your own"",
                          ""displayTime"": 25.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""custom controls in Windows Forms with complete"",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""control over the appearance and behavior of"",
                          ""displayTime"": 31.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""those controls."",
                          ""displayTime"": 34.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We also saw how you can take advantage of the"",
                          ""displayTime"": 36.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""full capabilities of the Windows operating system"",
                          ""displayTime"": 38.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""by calling into APIs with Platform Invoke."",
                          ""displayTime"": 41.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Two options that may be of interest to you,"",
                          ""displayTime"": 46.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""particularly if you're trying to migrate away from"",
                          ""displayTime"": 48.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms, are to host web content using"",
                          ""displayTime"": 50.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""the web browser control or to host"",
                          ""displayTime"": 54.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""WPF content with the ElementHost control."",
                          ""displayTime"": 57.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Both of these two options provide a potential"",
                          ""displayTime"": 61.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""way that you could migrate your application"",
                          ""displayTime"": 64.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""incrementally to more modern user interface"",
                          ""displayTime"": 66.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""frameworks, retiring some old parts of your"",
                          ""displayTime"": 69.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Windows Forms application and replacing them"",
                          ""displayTime"": 72.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""with equivalents written in new technologies."",
                          ""displayTime"": 75.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""So, with these recommendations, what I wanted"",
                          ""displayTime"": 79.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""to demonstrate is that you shouldn't feel like you're"",
                          ""displayTime"": 81.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""limited and constrained with Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 84.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""There's a lot of options available to you for"",
                          ""displayTime"": 87.1804112
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""going beyond the basic capabilities of Windows Forms."",
                          ""displayTime"": 89.1804112
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      ""title"": ""The Demo Application"",
                      ""playerUrl"": ""//app.pluralsight.com/player?course=windows-forms-best-practices&author=mark-heath&name=windows-forms-best-practices-m8&clip=4&mode=live"",
                      ""segments"": [
                        {
                          ""text"": ""We've demonstrated all of these techniques by taking"",
                          ""displayTime"": 1.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""our demo application, which allows you to view"",
                          ""displayTime"": 4.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""podcast episodes and taking it from initially being"",
                          ""displayTime"": 7.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""a bit of a mess, with all the code in the code behind"",
                          ""displayTime"": 10.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""of main form, to refactoring it to Model-View-Presenter"",
                          ""displayTime"": 13.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""and applying these various best practices and techniques"",
                          ""displayTime"": 17.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""for extensibility."",
                          ""displayTime"": 21.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""If you're a Pluralsight Plus subscriber, then you"",
                          ""displayTime"": 23.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""will be able to download the source code at"",
                          ""displayTime"": 26.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""every stage of the demo and examine it."",
                          ""displayTime"": 28.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Although, one word of caution."",
                          ""displayTime"": 30.7231779
                        },
                        {
                          ""text"": ""Not all of the techniques that we discussed in"",
